{"title_page": "Thomas Beatie", "text_new": "{{short description|Speaker, author, and trans advocate}}\n\n<!--Per Wikipedia:Manual of style, use he/him to refer to Thomas Beatie throughout his life.-->\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Thomas Beatie\n| image       = Thomas Beatie p\u00e5 Stockholm Pride 2011.JPG\n| image_size  =\n| caption     = Thomas Beatie at [[Stockholm Pride]] 2011\n| birth_name  = <!--Not used when subject not notable before gender transition/reassignment; see WP:BIRTHNAME--> \n| birth_date  = {{birth year and age|1974}}{{r|Trebay}}<!--See WP:DOB for guidance on including full dates of birth-->\n| birth_place = [[Honolulu, Hawaii]], United States\n| death_place =\n| residence   = \n| nationality = American\n| spouse      = Nancy Gillespie (2003\u20132012) <br> Amber Nicholas (2016\u2013)\n| website     = {{URL|http://definenormal.com}}\n| children    = 4\n| footnotes   =\n}}\n'''Thomas Trace Beatie''' (born 1974{{r|Trebay}}) is an American [[public speaker]], [[author]], and advocate of [[transgender]] and sexuality issues, with a focus on transgender fertility and [[reproductive rights]].\n\nIn early 1997, Beatie [[coming out|came out]] as a [[trans man]]. Beatie had [[gender reassignment surgery]] in March 2002 and became known as \"the pregnant man\" after he became [[pregnant]] through artificial insemination in 2007.{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} Beatie chose to be pregnant because his wife Nancy was infertile, doing so with cryogenic donated sperm.<ref name=\"Beatie 2008a\">{{cite web |url=http://www.advocate.com/news/2008/03/14/labor-love |last=Beatie |first=Thomas |title=Labor of Love: Is society ready for this pregnant husband? |work=The Advocate |date=March 14, 2008 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}, hardcopy version April 8, 2008, p. 24.</ref><ref name=Laboroflove>[http://www.laboroflove.tv Labor of Love website] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100123085309/http://www.laboroflove.tv/ |date=2010-01-23 }}.</ref> Beatie has since given birth to three children.\n\nThe couple filed for divorce in 2012. The Beatie case is the first of its kind on record, where a documented legal male gave birth within a heterosexual marriage to a woman, and for the first time, a court challenged a marriage where the husband gave birth.\n\n==Early life==\nBorn Tracy LaGondino,{{r|Trebay}}<ref name=\"Pilkington\">{{cite news |last=Pilkington |first=Ed |title=Childbirth: Transgender man has his baby, naturally |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2008/jul/05/gender.usa |work=The Guardian |date=4 July 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"Feldberg\">{{cite book |last=Feldberg |first=Dov |editor-last=Legato |editor-first=Marianne J. |title=Principles of Gender-Specific Medicine: Gender in the Genomic Era |date=2017 |publisher=Academic Press |location=London |isbn=978-0-1280-3506-1 |page=61 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Principles_of_Gender_Specific_Medicine.html?id=khATDgAAQBAJ&q=thomas+beatie+tracy+lagondino |chapter=Fertility Treatment and Preservation in Transgender Men and Women}}</ref> Beatie grew up in [[Honolulu, Hawaii]], the first of two children. Beatie's mother was from [[San Francisco]], and of [[English people|English]], [[Irish people|Irish]], [[Scottish people|Scottish]], and [[Welsh people|Welsh]] descent. His father, of [[Koreans|Korean]] and [[Filipinos|Filipino]] descent, was born and raised in Hawaii.<ref name=\"Beatie 2008b\">{{cite book |last=Beatie |first=Thomas |title=Labor of Love: The Story of One Man's Extraordinary Pregnancy |date=2008 |publisher=Seal Press |location=Berkeley, Calif. |isbn=978-1-58005-287-0 |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Labor_of_Love.html?id=e5BoCe-IrSwC}}</ref>{{Page needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nBeatie writes that he started to self-identify with the [[male]] gender at age ten.<ref>[http://hollywoodlife.com/2010/09/24/pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-speaks-out-about-shiloh-dressing-like-a-boy-doesnt-mean-shilohs-transgender/ \"'Pregnant Man' Thomas Beatie Speaks About Shiloh: Dressing Like a Boy Doesn't Mean Shiloh's Transgender!\"] hollywoodlife.com. September 24, 2010</ref> As a teenager, Beatie was a model and [[Miss Hawaii Teen USA]] pageant finalist.<ref>[http://abcnews.go.com/Health/story?id=6244878&page=1#.UU8y5e1eH8t \"Barbara Walters Exclusive: Pregnant Man Expecting Second Child\"] abcnew.go.com, November 13, 2008.</ref>\n\nIn 1996, Beatie graduated from the [[University of Hawaii]] with a bachelor's degree in health science (pre-med) and later pursued an Executive MBA. He competed in full-contact fighting and was a black belt and tournament champion in [[Taekwondo]].<ref name=\"definenormal\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zw0g7fek9do |title=Pregnant Man - Thomas Beatie - Full-Contact Taekwondo Tournament |website=YouTube |date=November 23, 2011 |accessdate=November 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Transition==\nIn March 2002, Beatie underwent [[sex reassignment surgery (female-to-male)|sex reassignment surgery]] involving a [[double mastectomy]],{{r|Cavalcante}} also known as \"top surgery\",{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} and officially changed his [[sex marker]] from \"female\" to \"male\" on his state and federal identity documents.{{r|Worthen & Dirks}}<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite book |last=Forbes |first=Alexis |editor1-last=Peterson |editor1-first=Dana |editor2-last=Panfil |editor2-first=Vanessa R. |title=Handbook of LGBT Communities, Crime, and Justice |date=2013 |publisher=Springer Science+Business Media |location=New York |isbn=978-1-4614-9187-3 |page=399 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Handbook_of_LGBT_Communities_Crime_and_J.html?id=CuK5BAAAQBAJ&q=thomas+beatie |chapter=Define 'Sex': Legal Outcomes for Transgender Individuals in the United States}}</ref> Prior to marriage he officially changed his name, choosing ''Trace'' as a middle name based on his birth name, Tracy.{{r|Beatie 2008b}}{{rp|160}}\n\nBeatie married Nancy Gillespie in a legally valid heterosexual marriage in Hawaii on February 5, 2003.<ref name=\"about_beatie\">{{cite web |url=http://marriage.about.com/od/celebritymarriages/p/thomasbeatie.htm |title=Thomas Beatie and Nancy Roberts (Celebrity Marriage category) |publisher=about.com |date=2013-03-29 |accessdate=2013-05-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511104356/http://marriage.about.com/od/celebritymarriages/p/thomasbeatie.htm |archivedate=2013-05-11 }}</ref> Beatie was also listed as \"male\" on his health and life insurance policies. The couple moved to [[Bend, Oregon]] in 2005.{{r|Beatie 2008b}}{{Page needed|date=January 2020}} When the two decided to start a family, Beatie chose to carry the child, since Nancy was unable due to a prior [[hysterectomy]].{{r|Hilton-Morrow & Battles}} He was able to become pregnant, having retained his female reproductive organs.<ref name=\"Rutter & Schwartz\">{{cite book |last1=Rutter |first1=Virginia |last2=Schwartz |first2=Pepper |title=The Gender of Sexuality: Exploring Sexual Possibilities |date=2012 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |location=Lanham, Md. |isbn=978-0-7425-7003-0 |pages=121\u20132 |edition=2nd |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Gender_of_Sexuality.html?id=gbpIbqiEy2sC&q=thomas+beatie}}</ref> Beatie suspended [[Hormone replacement therapy (female-to-male)|testosterone hormone treatment]] in order to conceive twice with donor sperm, delivering both children without complications.{{r|Feldberg}}\n\nIn February 2012, Beatie elected to have [[Bottom surgery|\"lower\" surgery]], including the creation of a functional [[human penis|penis]].{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} The procedure, performed by transgender surgeon [[Marci Bowers]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedoctorstv.com/videolib/init/6620 |title=Video Library |publisher=Thedoctorstv.com |accessdate=2012-11-05|date=2012-05-09 }}</ref> was documented on his second appearance of ''[[The Doctors (talk show)|The Doctors]]'', in 2012.<ref name=\"surgery\">{{cite web |url=http://www.thedoctorstv.com/main/show_synopsis/1026?section=synopsis |title=Exclusive: The Pregnant Man's Shocking Update on The Doctors TV Show (air date 5-1-12), Synopsis |publisher=thedoctorstv.com |date=May 1, 2012|accessdate=May 29, 2013|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109001242/http://www.thedoctorstv.com/main/show_synopsis/1026?section=synopsis |archivedate=January 9, 2014 }}</ref> The procedure, called a ring [[metoidioplasty]], included transfer of tissue, elongation of the hormonally enlarged phallus, as well as [[Urethroplasty|urethral construction]] and lengthening.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://on.aol.com/video/thomas-beaties-gender-reassignment-post-surgery-concerns-517353981 |title=AOL On - Thomas Beatie's Gender Reassignment Post-Surgery Concerns |publisher=On.aol.com |accessdate=November 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n== Public profile ==\nBeatie received intense media attention after he wrote a first-person article in the national [[LGBT]] magazine ''[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]'' in 2008.<ref name=\"Hilton-Morrow & Battles\">{{cite book |last1=Hilton-Morrow |first1=Wendy |last2=Battles |first2=Kathleen |title=Sexual Identities and the Media: An Introduction |date=2015 |publisher=Routledge |location=New York |isbn=978-0-415-53296-9 |pages=244\u20135 |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Sexual_Identities_and_the_Media.html?id=WwXwBgAAQBAJ&q=%22thomas+beatie%22}}</ref><ref name=\"Cavalcante\">{{cite book |last=Cavalcante |first=Andre |title=Struggling for Ordinary: Media and Transgender Belonging in Everyday Life |date=2018 |publisher=NYU Press |isbn=978-1-4798-8130-7 |pages=72\u20133 |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Struggling_for_Ordinary.html?id=9bRGDwAAQBAJ&q=%22thomas+beatie%22}}</ref> He wrote, \"our situation sparks legal, political, and social unknowns [...] Doctors have discriminated against us, turning us away due to their religious beliefs\".{{r|Beatie 2008b}}{{rp|265\u20136}}{{r|Beatie 2008a|Rutter & Schwartz}} The article was accompanied by a shirtless photograph of the pregnant Beatie,{{r|Cavalcante}} which became an object of [[voyeurism]] among the public according to the queer theorist [[Jack Halberstam]].{{r|Hilton-Morrow & Battles}} Within weeks of the online publication, news of his story quickly spread through national<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.katu.com/news/local/17002811.html?tab=video&c=y |title=Is the story of a pregnant man legit? |publisher=katu.com |date=2008-03-25 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MNkZhcmorOw |title=CNN reports pregnant man Thomas Beatie |publisher=YouTube.com |date=2008-04-04 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> and international media,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/quotes/0,26174,1725808,00.html |title=Time World: Quotes of the Day |publisher=time.com |date=2008-03-27 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> who dubbed Beatie \"the pregnant man\".{{r|Worthen & Dirks|Forbes}}\n\nThe media attention challenged many people's ideas about sex and gender, and attracted criticism of Beatie's identity and motives. Sociologist [[Lisa Wade]] wrote, \"I'm not sure what to make, sociologically, of the attention that Thomas' pregnancy is receiving in the mass media, but it is ripe for analysis\".{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} Many media outlets treated Beatie's pregnancy as a \"freak show\", according to media scholar Andre Cavalcante.{{r|Cavalcante}} The story helped promote transgender issues in the media; other [[trans men]] had given birth before Beatie, but were neither reported on nor legally recognized as male.{{r|Feldberg}}\n\nIn April 2008, Beatie made his first television appearance, an hour-long exclusive interview, on the ''[[Oprah Winfrey Show]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/people-oprah-exclusive-the-pregnant-man-speaks-out/|title=PEOPLE & Oprah Exclusive: The Pregnant Man Speaks Out |work=People|date=April 2, 2008|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref> During the show, he talked about his sense of reproductive right to bear a child independent of his male gender identity. He commented, \"It's not a male or female desire to want to have a child [...] it's a human desire [...] I'm a person, and I have the right to have my own biological child.\"{{r|Feldberg|Cavalcante}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oprah.com/oprahshow/Top-14-Most-Unlikely-Oprah-Shows-in-25-Years/11 |title=14 Most Unlikely Oprah Shows |website=Oprah |date=March 31, 2011|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> The ''Oprah'' episode received a spike in [[Nielsen ratings]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadcastingcable.com/article/113307-Syndication_Ratings_Pregnant_Man_Sends_Oprah_Back_to_Stratosphere.php |title=Syndication Ratings: Pregnant Man Sends Oprah Back to Stratosphere |website=Broadcasting & Cable |date=April 15, 2008|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> In the April 14, 2008, edition of ''[[People (magazine)]]'', Beatie was photographed by [[Mary Ellen Mark]] for a six-page story.<ref>{{cite web|title=People Magazine's \"He's Having a Baby\"|url=http://www.maryellenmark.com/text/magazines/people_new/918W-000-054.html|work=Mary Ellen Mark|accessdate=1 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/premium/april-14-2008/|title=April 14, 2008 |work=People|date=April 3, 2008|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>{{pb}}Beatie delivered his first child, Susan, on June 29, 2008.<ref name=\"Worthen & Dirks\">{{cite book |last1=Worthen |first1=Meredith G. F. |last2=Dirks |first2=Danielle |title=Sexual Deviance and Society: A sociological examination |date=2016 |publisher=Routledge |location=Abingdon, UK |isbn=978-1-1388-1906-1 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Sexual_Deviance_and_Society.html?id=cctTDAAAQBAJ&q=%22pregnant+man%22+beatie |chapter=Gender and Deviance}}</ref> Multiple tabloids, magazines, and other news outlets reported the story after paparazzi captured images of the family leaving the at the [[St. Charles Medical Center (Bend, Oregon)|St. Charles Medical Center]] in Bend, Oregon days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/pregnant-man-gives-birth-to-bouncing-baby-girl-and-father-and-daughter-are-doing-well-6825522.html |title=Pregnant Man gives birth to bouncing baby girl\u2026 and father and daughter are 'doing well' |publisher=standard.co.uk |date=July 4, 2008|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2008/07/03/pregnant-man-no-longer-pregnant/ |title=TMZ: Pregnant Man No Longer Pregnant! |publisher=tmz.com |date=2008-07-03 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''People'''s senior editor, Patrick Rogers, gave an interview to the CBS ''[[CBS Morning News#CBS Early Morning News.2Fcurrent Morning News format|Early Morning Show]]'' about the birth.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/video/watch/?id=4234033n |title=CBS: 'Pregnant Man' Gives Birth |publisher=CBS News|date=July 4, 2008|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''People''{{'}}s August 4, 2008, edition featured Beatie with his daughter, Susan, sharing the cover with a larger image of [[Barack Obama]], who at the time was a presidential candidate in the [[2008 United States presidential election|2008 U.S. presidential election]], posing with his family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.people.com/people/archive/jpgs/20080804/20080804-750-0.jpg |title=People Magazine cover for August 4, 2008 |work=People|date=August 4, 2008|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/the-pregnant-man-gives-birth-daddys-little-princess-vol-70-no-5/|title=The Pregnant Man Gives Birth \"Daddy's Little Princess\"|work=People|first=Champ|last=Clark|date=August 4, 2008|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>{{pb}}\n\nOn November 13, 2008, journalist [[Barbara Walters]] announced on ''[[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]]'' that Thomas was expecting his second child, Austin Alexander Beatie.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=irO68bI6i3g |title=The View talks about Pregnant Man|publisher=ABC|date=November 13, 2008|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref> The next day, ABC aired a 20/20 Barbara Walters primetime interview (\"Journey of a Pregnant Man\") with the Beaties.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/2020/video?id=6257558 |title=What Is a Man? What Is a Woman? |website=ABC News |date=2008-11-14 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jho1UCPDqXg |title=Journey of a Pregnant Man (1 of 5)|website=YouTube|date=October 29, 2009 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> During the interview, Walters showed a series of photographs of Beatie, commenting on the \"disturbing\" nature of the images, many of which highlighted his pregnant belly.{{r|Hilton-Morrow & Battles}}{{pb}}In June 2009, Beatie gave birth to his second child, a son.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/2020/story?id=7795344&page=1#.UaZzdOuhBUM |title=Exclusive: 'Pregnant Man' Gives Birth to Second Child |website=ABC News|date=2009-06-09 |accessdate=2013-05-29}}</ref> The couple's third child, a second son was born in July 2010.<ref name=\"about\">{{cite web |url=http://marriage.about.com/od/celebritymarriages/p/thomasbeatie.htm |title=Thomas Beatie and Nancy Roberts] (Celebrity Marriage category) |website=about.com |date=2013-03-29 |accessdate=2013-05-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511104356/http://marriage.about.com/od/celebritymarriages/p/thomasbeatie.htm |archivedate=2013-05-11 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TixtVKWZTrY |title=Pregnant Man's - Thomas Beatie's - Third Baby - Official Page |publisher=YouTube.com |date=2010-07-31 |accessdate=2013-05-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.perthnow.com.au/news/first-known-transgender-man-to-give-birth-delivers-third-child/story-e6frg12c-1225900419051 |title=First known transgender man to give birth delivers third child |date=2010-08-03 |publisher=perth now |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100805180922/http://www.perthnow.com.au/news/first-known-transgender-man-to-give-birth-delivers-third-child/story-e6frg12c-1225900419051 |archivedate=2010-08-05 }}</ref>\n\n''Guinness World Records'' 2010, named Beatie the \"World's First Married Man to Give Birth\".{{r|Worthen & Dirks}}<ref>\"First Married Man to Give Birth\", ''Guinness World Records'', 2010 edition, p 110\"</ref> In a TV broadcast from Rome, Italy, ''Guinness World Records'' presented him with the title of \"Unico Uomo Incinto al Mondo,\" translated as \"World's First Pregnant Man.\"<ref>[http://www.tvblog.it/galleria/lo-show-dei-record-2010-terza-puntata-sec-parte/59 ''Guinness World Records'', Italy (Lo Show Dei Record, 2010)] tvblog.it, Originally posted Sunday April 11, 2010</ref>\n\nOther TV appearances for Beatie include ''[[Larry King Live]]'' with [[Larry King]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2008/US/11/18/lkl.beatie.qanda/index.html?iref=allsearch#cnnSTCVideo |title='Pregnant Man' and wife: We're a normal couple |publisher=cnn.com |date=2008-11-17 |accessdate=2013-05-29}}</ref> ''[[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4WypyNaw4TM |title=Thomas Beatie and Family on The View 11-19-08 |publisher=YouTube.com |date=December 20, 2011 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Good Morning America]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BokX5u4dyx8 |title=Thomas Beatie on GMA with Kate Snow |website=YouTube|date=December 20, 2011|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Anderson Live]]'' with [[Anderson Cooper]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.andersoncooper.com/2012/11/15/videos-snooki-loves-being-a-mom-bow-wow-talks-fatherhood-and-more/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130628104603/http://www.andersoncooper.com/2012/11/15/videos-snooki-loves-being-a-mom-bow-wow-talks-fatherhood-and-more/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=June 28, 2013 |title=Anderson Live: 'Pregnant Man' on His Complicated Divorce |website=YouTube|date=November 15, 2012|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Oprah: Where Are They Now?]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oprah.com/own-where-are-they-now/The-Pregnant-Mans-Life-Today-Video |title=Own: The Pregnant Man's Life Today |publisher=YouTube.com |date=2012-11-27 |accessdate=2013-05-29}}</ref> and repeat features on ''The Doctors''<ref name=\"surgery\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thedoctorstv.com/main/show_synopsis/877?section=synopsis |title=The Doctors -- The Pregnant Man: After the Baby Show Synopsis |publisher=thedoctorstv.com |date=2011-10-31 |accessdate=May 29, 2013|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109023234/http://www.thedoctorstv.com//main/show_synopsis/877?section=synopsis |archivedate=January 9, 2014 }}</ref> and ''[[Dr. Drew]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hlntv.com/video/2012/05/17/who-do-pregnant-mans-kids-call-him |title=What do Pregnant Man's kids call him? |publisher=hlntv.com  |date=May 18, 2012|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hlntv.com/video/2012/08/14/pregnant-mans-divorce-struggle |title='Pregnant Man' on divorce: 'I'm confused' |publisher=hlntv.com  |date=August 15, 2012 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> Beatie has made personal appearances on over a dozen hit international TV talk shows in other countries such as Spain, Greece, Germany, Italy, Romania, Russia, Japan, Sweden, Poland, and the UK.<ref name=\"definenormal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.definenormal.com/PregnantMan/Home.html |title=Thomas Beatie World Public Speaker, Author, Educator, Advocate, Producer, Pop Culture Icon|publisher=Definenormal.com |accessdate=2012-11-05}}</ref>\n\nBetween August and November 2016, he was a contestant in the [[Secret Story 10 (France)|tenth season]] of [[Secret Story (French TV series)|Secret Story]], the French adaptation of Big Brother; his secret was \"I'm the first pregnant man ever\". He placed 2nd of all the contestants with 28% of the televote in the final.\n\nBeatie owns a website and T-shirt company featuring the slogan \"Define Normal\",{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} and has given keynote speeches at colleges and universities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.northbynorthwestern.com/story/thomas-beatie-discusses-pregnancies-lgbt-issues/ |title=Thomas Beatie discusses pregnancies, LGBT issues' at Northwestern University|publisher=northbynorthwestern.com  |date=February 24, 2013|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.americanownews.com/story/21926493/pregnant-man-speaks-at-uts-diversity-week |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130628105059/http://www.americanownews.com/story/21926493/pregnant-man-speaks-at-uts-diversity-week |url-status=dead |archive-date=June 28, 2013|title='Pregnant man' speaks at UT's Diversity Week (air date 5-1-12), Synopsis |website=America Now News|date=April 9, 2013 |accessdate=2013-05-29 }}</ref>\n\n==Legal precedent and divorce==\nOn March 8, 2012, Beatie filed a Petition for Legal Separation in Maricopa County, Arizona.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://radaronline.com/exclusives/2012/11/pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-opens-struggle-more-children-anderson-cooper/ |title='Pregnant Man' Thomas Beatie Opens Up About His Struggle To Have More Children |website=RadarOnline|date=November 24, 2012|accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref> Shortly after, Nancy converted the motion to a divorce. News of the break-up with his wife was leaked to tabloids during an April taping of the talk show ''The Doctors''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/pregnant-man-separates-from-wife/ |title=Pregnant Man Thomas Beatie and Wife Separate |work=People|date=April 19, 2012|accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref> Nancy was restricted to two-hour supervised visits with the children three times per week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2012/04/26/pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-divorce-abuse-punch-crotch-nancy/ |title=Pregnant Man: My Abusive Wife Punched Me... IN THE CROTCH |work=TMZ|date=April 26, 2013|accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref> On May 16, 2012, Thomas was awarded temporary sole custody of his three children and ordered to pay alimony to Nancy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2012/5/prweb9539522.htm |title=Arizona Court Recognizes Transgender Marriage: World's First Married Pregnant Man Is Awarded Sole Legal Child Custody |publisher=prweb.com \u00a0|date=May 24, 2012|accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"alimony\">{{cite web|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2012/8/prweb9833344.htm |title=Pregnant Man Thomas Beatie's Divorce Judge Orders Expert Testimony on Marriage Legality |publisher=prweb.com |date=August 24, 2012 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\nDuring the divorce proceedings, the presiding judge stated that because Beatie had given birth to the couple's children, he was legally female and therefore the marriage was not recognized in the state.{{r|Forbes}} Arizona Superior Court Judge Douglas Gerlach issued a [[nunc pro tunc]] Order questioning whether the Court had jurisdiction over the matter. The Beatie case was the first of its kind on record, where a documented legal male gave birth within a traditional marriage to a woman, and the first time a court challenged a marriage based upon a husband giving birth.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.azfamily.com/news/Pregnant-man-in-divorce-court-for-precedent-setting-case-189323871.html |title=Pregnant Man in divorce court for precedent-setting case |website=AZ Family |date=2013-02-01 |accessdate=May 28, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130204032154/http://www.azfamily.com/news/Pregnant-man-in-divorce-court-for-precedent-setting-case-189323871.html |archivedate=2013-02-04 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2012/12/12/pregnant-mans-divorce-case/1765359/ |title='Pregnant Man's' divorce case leaves judge in doubt |work=USA Today |date=December 12, 2012 |accessdate=May 28, 2013|first=Michael |last=Kiefer}}</ref> At the time, Arizona did not legally recognize same-sex marriage, so if Beatie were found to be female according to Arizona statute, the ten-year Beatie marriage would not be recognized in that state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salisburypost.com/article/20130102/SP01/130109944/ |title=Questions over sex change snag Arizona divorce case |work=Salisbury Post  |date=January 2, 2013 |accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref>\n\nBeatie's attorneys at the Cantor Law Group filed a memorandum showing that under Arizona State Statute, a transgender man's legal definition is set by certain medical operations, treatments, and finally a certified doctor's approval. \"Since Arizona and Hawaii have virtually the same Sex Change Statute, in this case we will prove that under the law Thomas was a man at the time of his wedding. Sterilization is not a requirement of either State's Statute. Under both Arizona's and Hawaii's law Thomas was a man at the time of his marriage, and therefore his three children born during the marriage are legitimate,\" stated attorney, David Michael Cantor. On August 15, 2012, Judge Gerlach ordered an [[Preliminary hearing|Evidentiary Hearing]] and [[Oral Argument]] on 7 December 2012.<ref name=\"alimony\"/> The [[Transgender Law Center]] filed a [[Amicus curiae|friend-of-the-court brief]] for the December trial in support of the Beaties' marriage and believes that the case could be significant regarding marriage, divorce, and reproductive rights for transgender people in the state of Arizona and around the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://transgenderlawcenter.org/archives/3038 |title=Thomas Beatie Marriage Case |publisher=transgenderlawcenter.org |date=March 29, 2013 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref> Expert testimony was provided by Beatie's sex-reassignment surgeon, Dr. Michael Brownstein M.D., in which the doctor implied that gender is more psychological than [[Chromosome|chromosomal]]. He also attested that the chest reconstruction procedure Beatie had undergone qualified as a sex-change surgery.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.azcentral.com/community/phoenix/articles/20121211pregnant-man-beatie-legal-limbo.html?nclick_check=1 |title='Pregnant man' Thomas Beatie in legal limbo |publisher=azcentral.com |date=December 13, 2012 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January 2013, a trial was heard to determine custody, child support, and division of property and debts, even though Arizona is not a common-law state.<ref name=\"reuters\">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc15.com/dpp/news/region_phoenix_metro/central_phoenix/pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-appeals-no-divorce-ruling |title='Pregnant man', Thomas Beatie appeals no-divorce ruling |publisher=abc15.com |date=April 2, 2013|accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://marriage.laws.com/common-law-marriage-arizona |title=Common Law Marriage Arizona |publisher=laws.com  |accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref> Despite the marriage's being put into question, the courts proceeded with custody arrangements for the children because both Beatie and Nancy legally adopted each of their three children in Oregon, in the Oregon court orders, Thomas was also listed as \"father\" and Nancy was listed as \"mother\" on each birth certificate, and each spouse had equal parental rights to custody.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parentdish.co.uk/2012/03/07/astonishing-pictures-emerge-of-man-giving-birth-for-the-third-time-thomas-beatie/ |title=Astonishing pictures emerge of MAN giving birth for the THIRD time |publisher=parentdish.co.uk |date=March 7, 2012 |accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn March 28, 2013, the court ruled that it had a lack of [[subject-matter jurisdiction]] to grant the Beaties a divorce and that Arizona did not have to comply with accepting out-of-state birth or marriage certificates. Despite medical testimony stating otherwise, Judge Gerlach did not consider gender identity, hormone treatment, and chest reconstruction as a valid sex-change surgery, as grounds for successful gender transition. \"If adopted, (it) would lead to circumstances in which a person's sex can become a matter of whim and not a matter of any reasonable, objective standard or policy, which is precisely the kind of absurd result the law abhors.\" Beatie's attorney said the judgement contained several errors.<ref name=\"reuters\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.courthousenews.com/2013/04/01/56254.htm |title=Arizona 'Pregnant Man' Can't Get Divorced in Arizona |publisher=courthousenews.com |date=April 1, 2013 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref> The court also ruled to give Nancy joint legal decision-making, physical custody and equal parenting time, ordering Beatie to pay her nearly $240 month in child support. Since the marriage was not considered valid in Arizona alimony was not further enforced, though the division of property was.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nathanlawoffices.com/news/-pregnant-man--to-appeal-after-judge-denies-divorce-20130417.cfm |title=\"Pregnant Man\" to Appeal after Judge Denies Divorce |publisher=nathanlawoffices.com  |date=2012-04-17 |accessdate=2013-05-30}}</ref>\n\nHowever, in August 2014, an Arizona Appeals Court declared that the marriage of the Beaties was valid and therefore they can get divorced, stating that Beatie should not have had to be sterilized in order to be legally recognized as a man in Arizona or Hawaii.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/politics/transgender/2014/08/14/two-trans-men-come-away-major-court-victories|title=Two Trans Men Come Away With Major Court Victories|date=14 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nBeatie remarried to Amber Beatie and now lives in Phoenix, Arizona. Together they have one child, which she carried.<ref>[https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/worlds-first-pregnant-man-i-want-1296196 \"The World's First Pregnant Man: \"I Want More Kids, If My New Girlfriend Can't Get Pregnant, Then I Will!\"], ''Mirror'', September 2, 2012.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.insideedition.com/headlines/7813-pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-is-having-another-child%3famp |title=Pregnant Man Thomas Beatie is Having Another Child |date=February 18, 2014 |website=Inside Edition |url-status=live}}{{Cite web |url=http://www.insideedition.com/headlines/7813-pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-is-having-another-child%3famp |title=Pregnant Man Thomas Beatie is Having Another Child |date=February 18, 2014 |website=Inside Edition |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== LGBT activism ==\nIn 2000\u20132001, Beatie was the co-chair and media chair for the Civil Unions-Civil Rights Movement in Honolulu, Hawaii, a non-profit [[LGBT]] organization for marriage equality. He helped organize and implement an island-wide, seven-day, 110-mile March for Equality.<ref>[http://archives.starbulletin.com/2001/01/13/news/story8.html Round-the-isle March Seeks End to Bias Against Gays] StarBulletin.com. January 13, 2001.</ref><ref>[http://archives.starbulletin.com/2001/01/23/news/story5.html \"Downtown Park Hosts Two Groups of Believers]\" StarBulletin.com. January 23, 2001.</ref> He also lobbied to pass the state's first [[Hate crime laws in the United States|Hate Crimes Law]]<ref>[http://the.honoluluadvertiser.com/article/2001/Jun/14/ln/ln25a.html Hirono Signs State's First Hate-crime Law] the.honoluluadvertiser.com. June 14, 2001.</ref><ref>[http://mphawaii.tripod.com/HateCrimesLaw/HateCrimesBill.pdf \"Acting Governor Hirono Signs Bill Toughening Sentences for Hate Crime Offenders\"], mphawaii.tripod.com.  June 13, 2001.</ref>(which passed in June, 2001), and worked as an advisor for the city and county's Chapter 19, an anti-bullying policy for the Board of Education.<ref>[https://lilinote.k12.hi.us/STATE/BOE/Minutes.nsf/ebb43af14ca5cdb30a2565cb006622a8/f2c8299700ca14b70a256b790061694d/$FILE/1-24-02%20BOE%20Minutes%20-%20Attachments.pdf Minutes of the State Board of Education Hawaii, Chapter 19 Committee, page 15] lilinote.k12.hi.us. Originally posted January 24, 2002.</ref>\n\nIn August 2011, he was the main opening speaker for [[Stockholm Pride]], speaking to an audience of tens of thousands. He also spearheaded one-on-one discussions with doctors, politicians, and policy-makers in support of abolishing the sterilization law for Swedish transgender people.<ref>[http://www.thelocal.se/35286/20110801/#.UT9fVO1eH8s \"Pregnant Man\" to Open Stockholm Pride] thelocal.se. Originally posted August 1, 2011 14:21 CET.</ref><ref>[http://www.stockholmpride.org/en/Journal/Festivalen-2011/Monday/Thomas-Beatie/ \"Meet Thomas Beatie\"] stockholmpride.org. August 2, 2011</ref><ref>[http://www.thelocal.se/35338/20110803/#.UU5PFe1eH8s \"Liberals Push for End to Sex Change Sterilisation\"] thelocal.se. August 3, 2011 16:15 CET</ref> [[Compulsory sterilisation in Sweden|Sweden's forced sterilization law]] for [[transgender people]] was overturned on December 19, 2012.<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/01/14/sweden-transgender-sterilization-law-overturned_n_2472925.html \"Sweden's Transgender Sterilization Law Overturned, Declared Unconstitutional\"] ''Huffington Post'' January 14, 2013</ref>\n\n== Cultural impact ==\nBeatie has challenged social and legal definitions of what constitutes being a man or a woman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indyweek.com/indyweek/how-to-wrap-your-head-around-the-pregnant-man/Content?oid=1208116 |title=How to Wrap Your Head Around the Pregnant Man |publisher=indyweek.com |date=2008-04-30 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Trebay\">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/22/fashion/22pregnant.html |title=He's Pregnant. You're Speechless |work=The New York Times |date=June 22, 2008 |first=Guy |last=Trebay}}</ref> ''People Magazine'' defines him as a pop culture icon in the magazine's special edition \"Pop Culture: 1000 Greatest Moments 1974 - 2011.\"<ref>Pop Culture: 1000 Greatest Moments 1974 - 2011 ''People''. PEOPLE 1000 Greatest Moments In Pop Culture 1974-2011 SPECIAL, page 132</ref> His legal case is also a precedent-setter for the ability of transgender people to exercise their constitutional right to reproduce and be recognized as his or her legal gender post sex-change transition.\n\n=== Sculpture ===\nIn May 2010, London sculptor [[Marc Quinn]] unveiled a 10-foot marble statue of Beatie when he was pregnant with daughter Susan. Marc Quinn commented, \"I think one of the main things to remember is that media attention and images are of their moment whereas Art is forever\u2026 that in 500 years time people will look at the beautiful marble sculpture of [Thomas] and have an emotional response and it will, I believe, somehow define something about our time.\"<ref name=\"definenormal\" />\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goodmenproject.com/featured-content/the-good-life-thomas-beatie-sculpted-in-marble/ |title=Behold the Pregnant Man |publisher=goodmenproject.com |date=2012-10-06 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tressugar.com/Marc-Quinn-Exhibit-Features-Sculptures-Pamela-Anderson-Thomas-Beatie-Michael-Jackson-8338526 |title=Marc Quinn Exhibit Features Sculptures of Pamela Anderson, Thomas Beatie, Michael Jackson |publisher=Tressugar.com |accessdate=2012-11-05}}</ref>\n\n=== Film ===\nThe documentary ''Pregnant Man'' (2008) documented the final weeks of Beatie's pregnancy and the birth of Susan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://health.discovery.com/tv-shows/specials/videos/pregnant-man-pregnant-man-on-discovery-health-channel.htm |title=Discovery Health \"Pregnant Man: Pregnant Man on Discovery Health Channel |publisher=health.discovery.com |accessdate=May 27, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EYX7ACuTBTY |title=The Pregnant Man - Pregnant Man's Diary - Channel 4 |publisher=YouTube.com  |date=2008-12-04 |accessdate=2013-05-30}}</ref> The documentary was the highest rated show for Discovery Networks for 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.collinsave.com/about-us |title=Collins Avenue, Executive Consultant for \"Pregnant Man\" documentary |publisher=collinsave.com |accessdate=2013-05-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140913205008/http://collinsave.com/about-us |archive-date=2014-09-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.septemberfilms.com/recentproductions.asp?id=209 |title=September Films production of the Pregnant Man documentary |publisher=septemberfilms.com |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=arc7FLzuouwU |title=Bloomberg Final Results for DCD Rights, distribution group for Pregnant Man documentary |publisher=bloomberg.com |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref> The documentary continues to screen worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadcastingcable.com/article/114488-Discovery_Exclusive_U_S_Rights_to_Pregnant_Man_Doc.php|title='Discovery: Exclusive U.S. Rights to Pregnant Man Doc |publisher=broadcastingcable.com |date=2008-07-10 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/11/us-beatie-idUSL107413020080711 |title='Pregnant Man' documentary in the works |publisher=reuters.com |date=2008-07-10 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref>\n\n=== Short film ===\nIn 2015, French director Jan Caplin wrote and directed the short movie ''Hippocampe'', inspired by Thomas Beatie and his wife's attempts to have a child.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jeunesse.gironde.fr/jeunesse/jcms/c_40811/court-metrage-hippocampe|title=D\u00e9partement de la Gironde - Court m\u00e9trage ''Hippocampe''|publisher=jeunesse.gironde.fr |date=2015-10-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://art-dn.wixsite.com/art-dn/hippocampe|title=Site de l'association Art DN - Hippocampe|publisher=art-dn.wixsite.com/art-dn/hippocampe|date=2015-06-02}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\nShortly after Susan was born, Beatie authored his first book, ''Labor of Love: The Story of One Man's Extraordinary Pregnancy'' (2008).{{r|Beatie 2008b}} In ''Labor of Love'', Beatie describes the fight for his right to have a child. ''Publisher's Weekly'' said the book was \"A compelling, unique narrative\". ''Book List'' praised it as \"Unforced and unpretentious,\" and the ''New York Times'' called it \"Defiant and transformative.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thomasbeatie.net |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121116004915/http://www.thomasbeatie.net/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-11-16 |title=Thomas Beatie's official book website |publisher=thomasbeatie.net |accessdate=2013-05-27 }}</ref>\n\n'''Other Works Include'''\n*  Thomas Beatie, \"Labor of Love: Is society ready for this pregnant husband?\" ''The Advocate''{{r|Beatie 2008a}}\n*  Book contribution, ''The New Transsexuals: The Next Step in Human Evolution'' by George Petros, Thomas Beatie, pp.&nbsp;34\u201343<ref>{{cite web|url=http://georgepetros.com/books/tnt.htm#.UVS8Tb-hD0c |title=The New Transsexuals -- The Next Step in Human Evolution, Thomas Beatie, pp. 34-43 (PetrosIdeas, 2012, pp. 34-43) ISBN 978-0-9855018-0-8 |publisher=georgepetros.com |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref>\n*  Swedish newspaper contribution to ''Aftonbladet''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/debatt/article13401439.ab |title=Sweden's Law Would Have Made Me Childless (translated from Swedish)|publisher=aftonbladet.se.com |date=2011-08-01 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref>\n*  Book contribution, ''Gender Identity and Sexual Orientation in the Workplace'' by Christine Duffy<ref>Gender Identity and Sexual Orientation in the Workplace by Christine Duffy, Beyond Binary essay by Thomas Beatie (2013)</ref>\n*  Thomas Beatie, \"Dad v. Scorpion,\" Goodmenproject.com<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goodmenproject.com/featured-content/the-good-life-dad-v-scorpion/ |title='Dad v. Scorpion by Thomas Beatie |publisher=goodmenproject.com |date=2013-01-05 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and honors ==\n*  [[Barbara Walters]] Top 10 Fascinating People of 2008<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.celebuzz.com/barbara-walters-names-most-fascinating-s68571/ |title=Barbara Walters Names Her Most Fascinating Friends |publisher=celebuzz.com |year=2008 |accessdate=2013-05-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121012141039/http://www.celebuzz.com/barbara-walters-names-most-fascinating-s68571/ |archive-date=2012-10-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*  [[Details (magazine)|''Details'' Magazine]]: 40 Most Influential Men in the World<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.details.com/culture-trends/critical-eye/200811/power-list-thomas-beatie |title=2008 Power List: 40. Thomas Beatie |publisher=details.com |year=2008 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref>\n*  20th Annual [[GLAAD Media Awards]] nominee: ''The Oprah Winfrey Show'', Outstanding Talk Show Episode nominee, \"The Pregnant Man\": subject Thomas Beatie<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thequod.blogspot.com/2009/01/spotlight-on-glaad-media-awards-2008.html |title=Spotlight on: The 2008 GLAAD Media Awards |publisher=thequod.blogspot.com |date=2009-01-27 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref>\n*  2009 ''Time'' Magazine: [[Time 100]]  Finalist<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,1883644_1883653_1883921,00.html |title=The 2009 Time 100 Finalists: The Pregnant Man--Thomas Beatie |work=TIME|accessdate=2013-05-28 |date=2009-03-19}}</ref>\n*  ''People Magazine'': Pop Culture 1000 Greatest Moments 1974 - 2011<ref>''People''. 1000 Greatest Moments In Pop Culture 1974-2011 SPECIAL, page 132</ref>\n*  2008 ''People Magazine'': 11 Most Shocking Moments<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/11-most-shocking-moments-of-2008/ |title=11 Most Shocking Moments of 2008 |work=People |date=November 20, 2008|accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref>\n*  ''Advocate'' Magazine: People of the Year 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/news/2008/12/02/wanda-sykes-thomas-beatie-kick-advocates-people-year?page=0,1 |title=Wanda Sykes, Thomas Beatie Kick Off Advocate's People of the Year |publisher=advocate.com |date=2008-12-02 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref>\n*  ''Time'' Magazine: The Top 10 Everything of 2008: Top 10 Oddball News Stories: #1 The Pregnant Man<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,1855948_1862262_1862270,00.html |title=The Top 10 Everything 2008: Top 10 Oddball News Stories, #1 Pregnant Man |publisher=time.com |date=2008-11-03 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref>\n*  ''Huffington Post'': Top 20 Trans Pioneer of 2011<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/11/20/transgender-day-of-remembrance-2011_n_1101681.html#s475756&title=Thomas_Beatie |title=Transgender Day of Remembrance 2011: 20 Trans Pioneers, Thomas Beatie |publisher=huffingtonpost.com |date=2011-11-20 |accessdate=2013-05-28 |first=Noah |last=Michelson}}</ref>\n* Handsome Men (Who Were Born Female)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oddee.com/item_98038.aspx |title=10 Handsome Men (Who Were Born Female), Thomas Beatie |publisher=oddee.com |date=2012-01-18 |accessdate=2013-05-28}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.ThomasBeatie.com The Official Thomas Beatie Website]\n*{{IMDb name|2976126}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Beatie, Thomas}}\n[[Category:People from Oahu]]\n[[Category:Transgender and transsexual men]]\n[[Category:1974 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:LGBT rights activists from the United States]]\n[[Category:Transgender and transsexual writers]]\n[[Category:LGBT writers from the United States]]\n[[Category:Transgender rights activists]]\n[[Category:American people of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Filipino descent]]\n[[Category:People from Bend, Oregon]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Welsh descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:LGBT American people of Asian descent]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Hawaii]]\n[[Category:University of Hawaii alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Speaker, author, and trans advocate}}\n\n<!--Per Wikipedia:Manual of style, use he/him to refer to Thomas Beatie throughout his life.-->\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Thomas Beatie\n| image       = Thomas Beatie p\u00e5 Stockholm Pride 2011.JPG\n| image_size  =\n| caption     = Thomas Beatie at [[Stockholm Pride]] 2011\n| birth_name  = <!--Not used when subject not notable before gender transition/reassignment; see WP:BIRTHNAME--> \n| birth_date  = {{birth year and age|1974}}{{r|Trebay}}<!--See WP:DOB for guidance on including full dates of birth-->\n| birth_place = [[Honolulu, Hawaii]], United States\n| death_place =\n| residence   = \n| nationality = American\n| spouse      = Nancy Gillespie (2003\u20132012) <br> Amber Nicholas (2016\u2013)\n| website     = {{URL|http://definenormal.com}}\n| children    = 4\n| footnotes   =\n}}\n'''Thomas Trace Beatie''' (born 1974{{r|Trebay}}) is an American [[public speaker]], [[author]], and advocate of [[transgender]] and sexuality issues, with a focus on transgender fertility and [[reproductive rights.]]\n\nIn early 1997, Beatie [[coming out|came out]] as a [[trans man]]. Beatie had [[gender reassignment surgery]] in March 2002 and became known as \"the pregnant man\" after he became [[pregnant]] through artificial insemination in 2007.{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} Beatie chose to be pregnant because his wife Nancy was infertile, doing so with cryogenic donated sperm.<ref name=\"Beatie 2008a\">{{cite web |url=http://www.advocate.com/news/2008/03/14/labor-love |last=Beatie |first=Thomas |title=Labor of Love: Is society ready for this pregnant husband? |work=The Advocate |date=March 14, 2008 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}, hardcopy version April 8, 2008, p. 24.</ref><ref name=Laboroflove>[http://www.laboroflove.tv Labor of Love website] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100123085309/http://www.laboroflove.tv/ |date=2010-01-23 }}.</ref> Beatie has since given birth to three children.\n\nThe couple filed for divorce in 2012. The Beatie case is the first of its kind on record, where a documented legal male gave birth within a heterosexual marriage to a woman, and for the first time, a court challenged a marriage where the husband gave birth.\n\n==Early life==\nBorn Tracy LaGondino,{{r|Trebay}}<ref name=\"Pilkington\">{{cite news |last=Pilkington |first=Ed |title=Childbirth: Transgender man has his baby, naturally |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2008/jul/05/gender.usa |work=The Guardian |date=4 July 2008}}</ref><ref name=\"Feldberg\">{{cite book |last=Feldberg |first=Dov |editor-last=Legato |editor-first=Marianne J. |title=Principles of Gender-Specific Medicine: Gender in the Genomic Era |date=2017 |publisher=Academic Press |location=London |isbn=978-0-1280-3506-1 |page=61 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Principles_of_Gender_Specific_Medicine.html?id=khATDgAAQBAJ&q=thomas+beatie+tracy+lagondino |chapter=Fertility Treatment and Preservation in Transgender Men and Women}}</ref> Beatie grew up in [[Honolulu, Hawaii]], the first of two children. Beatie's mother was from [[San Francisco]], and of [[English people|English]], [[Irish people|Irish]], [[Scottish people|Scottish]], and [[Welsh people|Welsh]] descent. His father, of [[Koreans|Korean]] and [[Filipinos|Filipino]] descent, was born and raised in Hawaii.<ref name=\"Beatie 2008b\">{{cite book |last=Beatie |first=Thomas |title=Labor of Love: The Story of One Man's Extraordinary Pregnancy |date=2008 |publisher=Seal Press |location=Berkeley, Calif. |isbn=978-1-58005-287-0 |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Labor_of_Love.html?id=e5BoCe-IrSwC}}</ref>{{Page needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nBeatie writes that he started to self-identify with the [[male]] gender at age ten.<ref>[http://hollywoodlife.com/2010/09/24/pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-speaks-out-about-shiloh-dressing-like-a-boy-doesnt-mean-shilohs-transgender/ \"'Pregnant Man' Thomas Beatie Speaks About Shiloh: Dressing Like a Boy Doesn't Mean Shiloh's Transgender!\"] hollywoodlife.com. September 24, 2010</ref> As a teenager, Beatie was a model and [[Miss Hawaii Teen USA]] pageant finalist.<ref>[http://abcnews.go.com/Health/story?id=6244878&page=1#.UU8y5e1eH8t \"Barbara Walters Exclusive: Pregnant Man Expecting Second Child\"] abcnew.go.com, November 13, 2008.</ref>\n\nIn 1996, Beatie graduated from the [[University of Hawaii]] with a bachelor's degree in health science (pre-med) and later pursued an Executive MBA. He competed in full-contact fighting and was a black belt and tournament champion in [[Taekwondo]].<ref name=\"definenormal\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zw0g7fek9do |title=Pregnant Man - Thomas Beatie - Full-Contact Taekwondo Tournament |website=YouTube |date=November 23, 2011 |accessdate=November 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Transition==\nIn March 2002, Beatie underwent [[sex reassignment surgery (female-to-male)|sex reassignment surgery]] involving a [[double mastectomy]],{{r|Cavalcante}} also known as \"top surgery\",{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} and officially changed his [[sex marker]] from \"female\" to \"male\" on his state and federal identity documents.{{r|Worthen & Dirks}}<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{cite book |last=Forbes |first=Alexis |editor1-last=Peterson |editor1-first=Dana |editor2-last=Panfil |editor2-first=Vanessa R. |title=Handbook of LGBT Communities, Crime, and Justice |date=2013 |publisher=Springer Science+Business Media |location=New York |isbn=978-1-4614-9187-3 |page=399 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Handbook_of_LGBT_Communities_Crime_and_J.html?id=CuK5BAAAQBAJ&q=thomas+beatie |chapter=Define 'Sex': Legal Outcomes for Transgender Individuals in the United States}}</ref> Prior to marriage he officially changed his name, choosing ''Trace'' as a middle name based on his birth name, Tracy.{{r|Beatie 2008b}}{{rp|160}}\n\nBeatie married Nancy Gillespie in a legally valid heterosexual marriage in Hawaii on February 5, 2003.<ref name=\"about_beatie\">{{cite web |url=http://marriage.about.com/od/celebritymarriages/p/thomasbeatie.htm |title=Thomas Beatie and Nancy Roberts (Celebrity Marriage category) |publisher=about.com |date=2013-03-29 |accessdate=2013-05-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511104356/http://marriage.about.com/od/celebritymarriages/p/thomasbeatie.htm |archivedate=2013-05-11 }}</ref> Beatie was also listed as \"male\" on his health and life insurance policies. The couple moved to [[Bend, Oregon]] in 2005.{{r|Beatie 2008b}}{{Page needed|date=January 2020}} When the two decided to start a family, Beatie chose to carry the child, since Nancy was unable due to a prior [[hysterectomy]].{{r|Hilton-Morrow & Battles}} He was able to become pregnant, having retained his female reproductive organs.<ref name=\"Rutter & Schwartz\">{{cite book |last1=Rutter |first1=Virginia |last2=Schwartz |first2=Pepper |title=The Gender of Sexuality: Exploring Sexual Possibilities |date=2012 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |location=Lanham, Md. |isbn=978-0-7425-7003-0 |pages=121\u20132 |edition=2nd |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Gender_of_Sexuality.html?id=gbpIbqiEy2sC&q=thomas+beatie}}</ref> Beatie suspended [[Hormone replacement therapy (female-to-male)|testosterone hormone treatment]] in order to conceive twice with donor sperm, delivering both children without complications.{{r|Feldberg}}\n\nIn February 2012, Beatie elected to have [[Bottom surgery|\"lower\" surgery]], including the creation of a functional [[human penis|penis]].{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} The procedure, performed by transgender surgeon [[Marci Bowers]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedoctorstv.com/videolib/init/6620 |title=Video Library |publisher=Thedoctorstv.com |accessdate=2012-11-05|date=2012-05-09 }}</ref> was documented on his second appearance of ''[[The Doctors (talk show)|The Doctors]]'', in 2012.<ref name=\"surgery\">{{cite web |url=http://www.thedoctorstv.com/main/show_synopsis/1026?section=synopsis |title=Exclusive: The Pregnant Man's Shocking Update on The Doctors TV Show (air date 5-1-12), Synopsis |publisher=thedoctorstv.com |date=May 1, 2012|accessdate=May 29, 2013|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109001242/http://www.thedoctorstv.com/main/show_synopsis/1026?section=synopsis |archivedate=January 9, 2014 }}</ref> The procedure, called a ring [[metoidioplasty]], included transfer of tissue, elongation of the hormonally enlarged phallus, as well as [[Urethroplasty|urethral construction]] and lengthening.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://on.aol.com/video/thomas-beaties-gender-reassignment-post-surgery-concerns-517353981 |title=AOL On - Thomas Beatie's Gender Reassignment Post-Surgery Concerns |publisher=On.aol.com |accessdate=November 5, 2012}}</ref>\n\n== Public profile ==\nBeatie received intense media attention after he wrote a first-person article in the national [[LGBT]] magazine ''[[The Advocate (LGBT magazine)|The Advocate]]'' in 2008.<ref name=\"Hilton-Morrow & Battles\">{{cite book |last1=Hilton-Morrow |first1=Wendy |last2=Battles |first2=Kathleen |title=Sexual Identities and the Media: An Introduction |date=2015 |publisher=Routledge |location=New York |isbn=978-0-415-53296-9 |pages=244\u20135 |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Sexual_Identities_and_the_Media.html?id=WwXwBgAAQBAJ&q=%22thomas+beatie%22}}</ref><ref name=\"Cavalcante\">{{cite book |last=Cavalcante |first=Andre |title=Struggling for Ordinary: Media and Transgender Belonging in Everyday Life |date=2018 |publisher=NYU Press |isbn=978-1-4798-8130-7 |pages=72\u20133 |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Struggling_for_Ordinary.html?id=9bRGDwAAQBAJ&q=%22thomas+beatie%22}}</ref> He wrote, \"our situation sparks legal, political, and social unknowns [...] Doctors have discriminated against us, turning us away due to their religious beliefs\".{{r|Beatie 2008b}}{{rp|265\u20136}}{{r|Beatie 2008a|Rutter & Schwartz}} The article was accompanied by a shirtless photograph of the pregnant Beatie,{{r|Cavalcante}} which became an object of [[voyeurism]] among the public according to the queer theorist [[Jack Halberstam]].{{r|Hilton-Morrow & Battles}} Within weeks of the online publication, news of his story quickly spread through national<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.katu.com/news/local/17002811.html?tab=video&c=y |title=Is the story of a pregnant man legit? |publisher=katu.com |date=2008-03-25 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MNkZhcmorOw |title=CNN reports pregnant man Thomas Beatie |publisher=YouTube.com |date=2008-04-04 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> and international media,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/quotes/0,26174,1725808,00.html |title=Time World: Quotes of the Day |publisher=time.com |date=2008-03-27 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> who dubbed Beatie \"the pregnant man\".{{r|Worthen & Dirks|Forbes}}\n\nThe media attention challenged many people's ideas about sex and gender, and attracted criticism of Beatie's identity and motives. Sociologist [[Lisa Wade]] wrote, \"I'm not sure what to make, sociologically, of the attention that Thomas' pregnancy is receiving in the mass media, but it is ripe for analysis\".{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} Many media outlets treated Beatie's pregnancy as a \"freak show\", according to media scholar Andre Cavalcante.{{r|Cavalcante}} The story helped promote transgender issues in the media; other [[trans men]] had given birth before Beatie, but were neither reported on nor legally recognized as male.{{r|Feldberg}}\n\nIn April 2008, Beatie made his first television appearance, an hour-long exclusive interview, on the ''[[Oprah Winfrey Show]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/tv/people-oprah-exclusive-the-pregnant-man-speaks-out/|title=PEOPLE & Oprah Exclusive: The Pregnant Man Speaks Out |work=People|date=April 2, 2008|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref> During the show, he talked about his sense of reproductive right to bear a child independent of his male gender identity. He commented, \"It's not a male or female desire to want to have a child [...] it's a human desire [...] I'm a person, and I have the right to have my own biological child.\"{{r|Feldberg|Cavalcante}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oprah.com/oprahshow/Top-14-Most-Unlikely-Oprah-Shows-in-25-Years/11 |title=14 Most Unlikely Oprah Shows |website=Oprah |date=March 31, 2011|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> The ''Oprah'' episode received a spike in [[Nielsen ratings]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadcastingcable.com/article/113307-Syndication_Ratings_Pregnant_Man_Sends_Oprah_Back_to_Stratosphere.php |title=Syndication Ratings: Pregnant Man Sends Oprah Back to Stratosphere |website=Broadcasting & Cable |date=April 15, 2008|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> In the April 14, 2008, edition of ''[[People (magazine)]]'', Beatie was photographed by [[Mary Ellen Mark]] for a six-page story.<ref>{{cite web|title=People Magazine's \"He's Having a Baby\"|url=http://www.maryellenmark.com/text/magazines/people_new/918W-000-054.html|work=Mary Ellen Mark|accessdate=1 December 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/premium/april-14-2008/|title=April 14, 2008 |work=People|date=April 3, 2008|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>{{pb}}Beatie delivered his first child, Susan, on June 29, 2008.<ref name=\"Worthen & Dirks\">{{cite book |last1=Worthen |first1=Meredith G. F. |last2=Dirks |first2=Danielle |title=Sexual Deviance and Society: A sociological examination |date=2016 |publisher=Routledge |location=Abingdon, UK |isbn=978-1-1388-1906-1 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Sexual_Deviance_and_Society.html?id=cctTDAAAQBAJ&q=%22pregnant+man%22+beatie |chapter=Gender and Deviance}}</ref> Multiple tabloids, magazines, and other news outlets reported the story after paparazzi captured images of the family leaving the at the [[St. Charles Medical Center (Bend, Oregon)|St. Charles Medical Center]] in Bend, Oregon days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/pregnant-man-gives-birth-to-bouncing-baby-girl-and-father-and-daughter-are-doing-well-6825522.html |title=Pregnant Man gives birth to bouncing baby girl\u2026 and father and daughter are 'doing well' |publisher=standard.co.uk |date=July 4, 2008|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2008/07/03/pregnant-man-no-longer-pregnant/ |title=TMZ: Pregnant Man No Longer Pregnant! |publisher=tmz.com |date=2008-07-03 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''People'''s senior editor, Patrick Rogers, gave an interview to the CBS ''[[CBS Morning News#CBS Early Morning News.2Fcurrent Morning News format|Early Morning Show]]'' about the birth.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/video/watch/?id=4234033n |title=CBS: 'Pregnant Man' Gives Birth |publisher=CBS News|date=July 4, 2008|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''People''{{'}}s August 4, 2008, edition featured Beatie with his daughter, Susan, sharing the cover with a larger image of [[Barack Obama]], who at the time was a presidential candidate in the [[2008 United States presidential election|2008 U.S. presidential election]], posing with his family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.people.com/people/archive/jpgs/20080804/20080804-750-0.jpg |title=People Magazine cover for August 4, 2008 |work=People|date=August 4, 2008|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/the-pregnant-man-gives-birth-daddys-little-princess-vol-70-no-5/|title=The Pregnant Man Gives Birth \"Daddy's Little Princess\"|work=People|first=Champ|last=Clark|date=August 4, 2008|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>{{pb}}\n\nOn November 13, 2008, journalist [[Barbara Walters]] announced on ''[[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]]'' that Thomas was expecting his second child, Austin Alexander Beatie.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=irO68bI6i3g |title=The View talks about Pregnant Man|publisher=ABC|date=November 13, 2008|accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref> The next day, ABC aired a 20/20 Barbara Walters primetime interview (\"Journey of a Pregnant Man\") with the Beaties.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/2020/video?id=6257558 |title=What Is a Man? What Is a Woman? |website=ABC News |date=2008-11-14 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jho1UCPDqXg |title=Journey of a Pregnant Man (1 of 5)|website=YouTube|date=October 29, 2009 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> During the interview, Walters showed a series of photographs of Beatie, commenting on the \"disturbing\" nature of the images, many of which highlighted his pregnant belly.{{r|Hilton-Morrow & Battles}}{{pb}}In June 2009, Beatie gave birth to his second child, a son.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/2020/story?id=7795344&page=1#.UaZzdOuhBUM |title=Exclusive: 'Pregnant Man' Gives Birth to Second Child |website=ABC News|date=2009-06-09 |accessdate=2013-05-29}}</ref> The couple's third child, a second son was born in July 2010.<ref name=\"about\">{{cite web |url=http://marriage.about.com/od/celebritymarriages/p/thomasbeatie.htm |title=Thomas Beatie and Nancy Roberts] (Celebrity Marriage category) |website=about.com |date=2013-03-29 |accessdate=2013-05-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130511104356/http://marriage.about.com/od/celebritymarriages/p/thomasbeatie.htm |archivedate=2013-05-11 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TixtVKWZTrY |title=Pregnant Man's - Thomas Beatie's - Third Baby - Official Page |publisher=YouTube.com |date=2010-07-31 |accessdate=2013-05-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.perthnow.com.au/news/first-known-transgender-man-to-give-birth-delivers-third-child/story-e6frg12c-1225900419051 |title=First known transgender man to give birth delivers third child |date=2010-08-03 |publisher=perth now |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100805180922/http://www.perthnow.com.au/news/first-known-transgender-man-to-give-birth-delivers-third-child/story-e6frg12c-1225900419051 |archivedate=2010-08-05 }}</ref>\n\n''Guinness World Records'' 2010, named Beatie the \"World's First Married Man to Give Birth\".{{r|Worthen & Dirks}}<ref>\"First Married Man to Give Birth\", ''Guinness World Records'', 2010 edition, p 110\"</ref> In a TV broadcast from Rome, Italy, ''Guinness World Records'' presented him with the title of \"Unico Uomo Incinto al Mondo,\" translated as \"World's First Pregnant Man.\"<ref>[http://www.tvblog.it/galleria/lo-show-dei-record-2010-terza-puntata-sec-parte/59 ''Guinness World Records'', Italy (Lo Show Dei Record, 2010)] tvblog.it, Originally posted Sunday April 11, 2010</ref>\n\nOther TV appearances for Beatie include ''[[Larry King Live]]'' with [[Larry King]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2008/US/11/18/lkl.beatie.qanda/index.html?iref=allsearch#cnnSTCVideo |title='Pregnant Man' and wife: We're a normal couple |publisher=cnn.com |date=2008-11-17 |accessdate=2013-05-29}}</ref> ''[[The View (U.S. TV series)|The View]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4WypyNaw4TM |title=Thomas Beatie and Family on The View 11-19-08 |publisher=YouTube.com |date=December 20, 2011 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Good Morning America]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BokX5u4dyx8 |title=Thomas Beatie on GMA with Kate Snow |website=YouTube|date=December 20, 2011|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Anderson Live]]'' with [[Anderson Cooper]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.andersoncooper.com/2012/11/15/videos-snooki-loves-being-a-mom-bow-wow-talks-fatherhood-and-more/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130628104603/http://www.andersoncooper.com/2012/11/15/videos-snooki-loves-being-a-mom-bow-wow-talks-fatherhood-and-more/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=June 28, 2013 |title=Anderson Live: 'Pregnant Man' on His Complicated Divorce |website=YouTube|date=November 15, 2012|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Oprah: Where Are They Now?]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oprah.com/own-where-are-they-now/The-Pregnant-Mans-Life-Today-Video |title=Own: The Pregnant Man's Life Today |publisher=YouTube.com |date=2012-11-27 |accessdate=2013-05-29}}</ref> and repeat features on ''The Doctors''<ref name=\"surgery\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thedoctorstv.com/main/show_synopsis/877?section=synopsis |title=The Doctors -- The Pregnant Man: After the Baby Show Synopsis |publisher=thedoctorstv.com |date=2011-10-31 |accessdate=May 29, 2013|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140109023234/http://www.thedoctorstv.com//main/show_synopsis/877?section=synopsis |archivedate=January 9, 2014 }}</ref> and ''[[Dr. Drew]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hlntv.com/video/2012/05/17/who-do-pregnant-mans-kids-call-him |title=What do Pregnant Man's kids call him? |publisher=hlntv.com  |date=May 18, 2012|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hlntv.com/video/2012/08/14/pregnant-mans-divorce-struggle |title='Pregnant Man' on divorce: 'I'm confused' |publisher=hlntv.com  |date=August 15, 2012 |accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref> Beatie has made personal appearances on over a dozen hit international TV talk shows in other countries such as Spain, Greece, Germany, Italy, Romania, Russia, Japan, Sweden, Poland, and the UK.<ref name=\"definenormal\">{{cite web|url=http://www.definenormal.com/PregnantMan/Home.html |title=Thomas Beatie World Public Speaker, Author, Educator, Advocate, Producer, Pop Culture Icon|publisher=Definenormal.com |accessdate=2012-11-05}}</ref>\n\nBetween August and November 2016, he was a contestant in the [[Secret Story 10 (France)|tenth season]] of [[Secret Story (French TV series)|Secret Story]], the French adaptation of Big Brother; his secret was \"I'm the first pregnant man ever\". He placed 2nd of all the contestants with 28% of the televote in the final.\n\nBeatie owns a website and T-shirt company featuring the slogan \"Define Normal\",{{r|Worthen & Dirks}} and has given keynote speeches at colleges and universities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.northbynorthwestern.com/story/thomas-beatie-discusses-pregnancies-lgbt-issues/ |title=Thomas Beatie discusses pregnancies, LGBT issues' at Northwestern University|publisher=northbynorthwestern.com  |date=February 24, 2013|accessdate=May 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.americanownews.com/story/21926493/pregnant-man-speaks-at-uts-diversity-week |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130628105059/http://www.americanownews.com/story/21926493/pregnant-man-speaks-at-uts-diversity-week |url-status=dead |archive-date=June 28, 2013|title='Pregnant man' speaks at UT's Diversity Week (air date 5-1-12), Synopsis |website=America Now News|date=April 9, 2013 |accessdate=2013-05-29 }}</ref>\n\n==Legal precedent and divorce==\nOn March 8, 2012, Beatie filed a Petition for Legal Separation in Maricopa County, Arizona.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://radaronline.com/exclusives/2012/11/pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-opens-struggle-more-children-anderson-cooper/ |title='Pregnant Man' Thomas Beatie Opens Up About His Struggle To Have More Children |website=RadarOnline|date=November 24, 2012|accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref> Shortly after, Nancy converted the motion to a divorce. News of the break-up with his wife was leaked to tabloids during an April taping of the talk show ''The Doctors''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/pregnant-man-separates-from-wife/ |title=Pregnant Man Thomas Beatie and Wife Separate |work=People|date=April 19, 2012|accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref> Nancy was restricted to two-hour supervised visits with the children three times per week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tmz.com/2012/04/26/pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-divorce-abuse-punch-crotch-nancy/ |title=Pregnant Man: My Abusive Wife Punched Me... IN THE CROTCH |work=TMZ|date=April 26, 2013|accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref> On May 16, 2012, Thomas was awarded temporary sole custody of his three children and ordered to pay alimony to Nancy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2012/5/prweb9539522.htm |title=Arizona Court Recognizes Transgender Marriage: World's First Married Pregnant Man Is Awarded Sole Legal Child Custody |publisher=prweb.com \u00a0|date=May 24, 2012|accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"alimony\">{{cite web|url=http://www.prweb.com/releases/2012/8/prweb9833344.htm |title=Pregnant Man Thomas Beatie's Divorce Judge Orders Expert Testimony on Marriage Legality |publisher=prweb.com |date=August 24, 2012 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\nDuring the divorce proceedings, the presiding judge stated that because Beatie had given birth to the couple's children, he was legally female and therefore the marriage was not recognized in the state.{{r|Forbes}} Arizona Superior Court Judge Douglas Gerlach issued a [[nunc pro tunc]] Order questioning whether the Court had jurisdiction over the matter. The Beatie case was the first of its kind on record, where a documented legal male gave birth within a traditional marriage to a woman, and the first time a court challenged a marriage based upon a husband giving birth.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.azfamily.com/news/Pregnant-man-in-divorce-court-for-precedent-setting-case-189323871.html |title=Pregnant Man in divorce court for precedent-setting case |website=AZ Family |date=2013-02-01 |accessdate=May 28, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130204032154/http://www.azfamily.com/news/Pregnant-man-in-divorce-court-for-precedent-setting-case-189323871.html |archivedate=2013-02-04 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2012/12/12/pregnant-mans-divorce-case/1765359/ |title='Pregnant Man's' divorce case leaves judge in doubt |work=USA Today |date=December 12, 2012 |accessdate=May 28, 2013|first=Michael |last=Kiefer}}</ref> At the time, Arizona did not legally recognize same-sex marriage, so if Beatie were found to be female according to Arizona statute, the ten-year Beatie marriage would not be recognized in that state.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salisburypost.com/article/20130102/SP01/130109944/ |title=Questions over sex change snag Arizona divorce case |work=Salisbury Post  |date=January 2, 2013 |accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref>\n\nBeatie's attorneys at the Cantor Law Group filed a memorandum showing that under Arizona State Statute, a transgender man's legal definition is set by certain medical operations, treatments, and finally a certified doctor's approval. \"Since Arizona and Hawaii have virtually the same Sex Change Statute, in this case we will prove that under the law Thomas was a man at the time of his wedding. Sterilization is not a requirement of either State's Statute. Under both Arizona's and Hawaii's law Thomas was a man at the time of his marriage, and therefore his three children born during the marriage are legitimate,\" stated attorney, David Michael Cantor. On August 15, 2012, Judge Gerlach ordered an [[Preliminary hearing|Evidentiary Hearing]] and [[Oral Argument]] on 7 December 2012.<ref name=\"alimony\"/> The [[Transgender Law Center]] filed a [[Amicus curiae|friend-of-the-court brief]] for the December trial in support of the Beaties' marriage and believes that the case could be significant regarding marriage, divorce, and reproductive rights for transgender people in the state of Arizona and around the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://transgenderlawcenter.org/archives/3038 |title=Thomas Beatie Marriage Case |publisher=transgenderlawcenter.org |date=March 29, 2013 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref> Expert testimony was provided by Beatie's sex-reassignment surgeon, Dr. Michael Brownstein M.D., in which the doctor implied that gender is more psychological than [[Chromosome|chromosomal]]. He also attested that the chest reconstruction procedure Beatie had undergone qualified as a sex-change surgery.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.azcentral.com/community/phoenix/articles/20121211pregnant-man-beatie-legal-limbo.html?nclick_check=1 |title='Pregnant man' Thomas Beatie in legal limbo |publisher=azcentral.com |date=December 13, 2012 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January 2013, a trial was heard to determine custody, child support, and division of property and debts, even though Arizona is not a common-law state.<ref name=\"reuters\">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc15.com/dpp/news/region_phoenix_metro/central_phoenix/pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-appeals-no-divorce-ruling |title='Pregnant man', Thomas Beatie appeals no-divorce ruling |publisher=abc15.com |date=April 2, 2013|accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://marriage.laws.com/common-law-marriage-arizona |title=Common Law Marriage Arizona |publisher=laws.com  |accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref> Despite the marriage's being put into question, the courts proceeded with custody arrangements for the children because both Beatie and Nancy legally adopted each of their three children in Oregon, in the Oregon court orders, Thomas was also listed as \"father\" and Nancy was listed as \"mother\" on each birth certificate, and each spouse had equal parental rights to custody.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parentdish.co.uk/2012/03/07/astonishing-pictures-emerge-of-man-giving-birth-for-the-third-time-thomas-beatie/ |title=Astonishing pictures emerge of MAN giving birth for the THIRD time |publisher=parentdish.co.uk |date=March 7, 2012 |accessdate=May 30, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn March 28, 2013, the court ruled that it had a lack of [[subject-matter jurisdiction]] to grant the Beaties a divorce and that Arizona did not have to comply with accepting out-of-state birth or marriage certificates. Despite medical testimony stating otherwise, Judge Gerlach did not consider gender identity, hormone treatment, and chest reconstruction as a valid sex-change surgery, as grounds for successful gender transition. \"If adopted, (it) would lead to circumstances in which a person's sex can become a matter of whim and not a matter of any reasonable, objective standard or policy, which is precisely the kind of absurd result the law abhors.\" Beatie's attorney said the judgement contained several errors.<ref name=\"reuters\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.courthousenews.com/2013/04/01/56254.htm |title=Arizona 'Pregnant Man' Can't Get Divorced in Arizona |publisher=courthousenews.com |date=April 1, 2013 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref> The court also ruled to give Nancy joint legal decision-making, physical custody and equal parenting time, ordering Beatie to pay her nearly $240 month in child support. Since the marriage was not considered valid in Arizona alimony was not further enforced, though the division of property was.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nathanlawoffices.com/news/-pregnant-man--to-appeal-after-judge-denies-divorce-20130417.cfm |title=\"Pregnant Man\" to Appeal after Judge Denies Divorce |publisher=nathanlawoffices.com  |date=2012-04-17 |accessdate=2013-05-30}}</ref>\n\nHowever, in August 2014, an Arizona Appeals Court declared that the marriage of the Beaties was valid and therefore they can get divorced, stating that Beatie should not have had to be sterilized in order to be legally recognized as a man in Arizona or Hawaii.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advocate.com/politics/transgender/2014/08/14/two-trans-men-come-away-major-court-victories|title=Two Trans Men Come Away With Major Court Victories|date=14 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nBeatie remarried to Amber Beatie and now lives in Phoenix, Arizona. Together they have one child, which she carried.<ref>[https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/worlds-first-pregnant-man-i-want-1296196 \"The World's First Pregnant Man: \"I Want More Kids, If My New Girlfriend Can't Get Pregnant, Then I Will!\"], ''Mirror'', September 2, 2012.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.insideedition.com/headlines/7813-pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-is-having-another-child%3famp |title=Pregnant Man Thomas Beatie is Having Another Child |date=February 18, 2014 |website=Inside Edition |url-status=live}}{{Cite web |url=http://www.insideedition.com/headlines/7813-pregnant-man-thomas-beatie-is-having-another-child%3famp |title=Pregnant Man Thomas Beatie is Having Another Child |date=February 18, 2014 |website=Inside Edition |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== LGBT activism ==\nIn 2000\u20132001, Beatie was the co-chair and media chair for the Civil Unions-Civil Rights Movement in Honolulu, Hawaii, a non-profit [[LGBT]] organization for marriage equality. He helped organize and implement an island-wide, seven-day, 110-mile March for Equality.<ref>[http://archives.starbulletin.com/2001/01/13/news/story8.html Round-the-isle March Seeks End to Bias Against Gays] StarBulletin.com. January 13, 2001.</ref><ref>[http://archives.starbulletin.com/2001/01/23/news/story5.html \"Downtown Park Hosts Two Groups of Believers]\" StarBulletin.com. January 23, 2001.</ref> He also lobbied to pass the state's first [[Hate crime laws in the United States|Hate Crimes Law]]<ref>[http://the.honoluluadvertiser.com/article/2001/Jun/14/ln/ln25a.html Hirono Signs State's First Hate-crime Law] the.honoluluadvertiser.com. June 14, 2001.</ref><ref>[http://mphawaii.tripod.com/HateCrimesLaw/HateCrimesBill.pdf \"Acting Governor Hirono Signs Bill Toughening Sentences for Hate Crime Offenders\"], mphawaii.tripod.com.  June 13, 2001.</ref>(which passed in June, 2001), and worked as an advisor for the city and county's Chapter 19, an anti-bullying policy for the Board of Education.<ref>[https://lilinote.k12.hi.us/STATE/BOE/Minutes.nsf/ebb43af14ca5cdb30a2565cb006622a8/f2c8299700ca14b70a256b790061694d/$FILE/1-24-02%20BOE%20Minutes%20-%20Attachments.pdf Minutes of the State Board of Education Hawaii, Chapter 19 Committee, page 15] lilinote.k12.hi.us. Originally posted January 24, 2002.</ref>\n\nIn August 2011, he was the main opening speaker for [[Stockholm Pride]], speaking to an audience of tens of thousands. He also spearheaded one-on-one discussions with doctors, politicians, and policy-makers in support of abolishing the sterilization law for Swedish transgender people.<ref>[http://www.thelocal.se/35286/20110801/#.UT9fVO1eH8s \"Pregnant Man\" to Open Stockholm Pride] thelocal.se. Originally posted August 1, 2011 14:21 CET.</ref><ref>[http://www.stockholmpride.org/en/Journal/Festivalen-2011/Monday/Thomas-Beatie/ \"Meet Thomas Beatie\"] stockholmpride.org. August 2, 2011</ref><ref>[http://www.thelocal.se/35338/20110803/#.UU5PFe1eH8s \"Liberals Push for End to Sex Change Sterilisation\"] thelocal.se. August 3, 2011 16:15 CET</ref> [[Compulsory sterilisation in Sweden|Sweden's forced sterilization law]] for [[transgender people]] was overturned on December 19, 2012.<ref>[http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/01/14/sweden-transgender-sterilization-law-overturned_n_2472925.html \"Sweden's Transgender Sterilization Law Overturned, Declared Unconstitutional\"] ''Huffington Post'' January 14, 2013</ref>\n\n== Cultural impact ==\nBeatie has challenged social and legal definitions of what constitutes being a man or a woman.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indyweek.com/indyweek/how-to-wrap-your-head-around-the-pregnant-man/Content?oid=1208116 |title=How to Wrap Your Head Around the Pregnant Man |publisher=indyweek.com |date=2008-04-30 |accessdate=May 28, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"Trebay\">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/22/fashion/22pregnant.html |title=He's Pregnant. You're Speechless |work=The New York Times |date=June 22, 2008 |first=Guy |last=Trebay}}</ref> ''People Magazine'' defines him as a pop culture icon in the magazine's special edition \"Pop Culture: 1000 Greatest Moments 1974 - 2011.\"<ref>Pop Culture: 1000 Greatest Moments 1974 - 2011 ''People''. PEOPLE 1000 Greatest Moments In Pop Culture 1974-2011 SPECIAL, page 132</ref> His legal case is also a precedent-setter for the ability of transgender people to exercise their constitutional right to reproduce and be recognized as his or her legal gender post sex-change transition.\n\n=== Sculpture ===\nIn May 2010, London sculptor [[Marc Quinn]] unveiled a 10-foot marble statue of Beatie when he was pregnant with daughter Susan. Marc Quinn commented, \"I think one of the main things to remember is that media attention and images are of their moment whereas Art is forever\u2026 that in 500 years time people will look at the beautiful marble sculpture of [Thomas] and have an emotional response and it will, I believe, somehow define something about our time.\"<ref name=\"definenormal\" />\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goodmenproject.com/featured-content/the-good-life-thomas-beatie-sculpted-in-marble/ |title=Behold the Pregnant Man |publisher=goodmenproject.com |date=2012-10-06 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tressugar.com/Marc-Quinn-Exhibit-Features-Sculptures-Pamela-Anderson-Thomas-Beatie-Michael-Jackson-8338526 |title=Marc Quinn Exhibit Features Sculptures of Pamela Anderson, Thomas Beatie, Michael Jackson |publisher=Tressugar.com |accessdate=2012-11-05}}</ref>\n\n=== Film ===\nThe documentary ''Pregnant Man'' (2008) documented the final weeks of Beatie's pregnancy and the birth of Susan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://health.discovery.com/tv-shows/specials/videos/pregnant-man-pregnant-man-on-discovery-health-channel.htm |title=Discovery Health \"Pregnant Man: Pregnant Man on Discovery Health Channel |publisher=health.discovery.com |accessdate=May 27, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EYX7ACuTBTY |title=The Pregnant Man - Pregnant Man's Diary - Channel 4 |publisher=YouTube.com  |date=2008-12-04 |accessdate=2013-05-30}}</ref> The documentary was the highest rated show for Discovery Networks for 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.collinsave.com/about-us |title=Collins Avenue, Executive Consultant for \"Pregnant Man\" documentary |publisher=collinsave.com |accessdate=2013-05-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140913205008/http://collinsave.com/about-us |archive-date=2014-09-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.septemberfilms.com/recentproductions.asp?id=209 |title=September Films production of the Pregnant Man documentary |publisher=septemberfilms.com |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=arc7FLzuouwU |title=Bloomberg Final Results for DCD Rights, distribution group for Pregnant Man documentary |publisher=bloomberg.com |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref> The documentary continues to screen worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.broadcastingcable.com/article/114488-Discovery_Exclusive_U_S_Rights_to_Pregnant_Man_Doc.php|title='Discovery: Exclusive U.S. Rights to Pregnant Man Doc |publisher=broadcastingcable.com |date=2008-07-10 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/11/us-beatie-idUSL107413020080711 |title='Pregnant Man' documentary in the works |publisher=reuters.com |date=2008-07-10 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref>\n\n=== Short film ===\nIn 2015, French director Jan Caplin wrote and directed the short movie ''Hippocampe'', inspired by Thomas Beatie and his wife's attempts to have a child.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jeunesse.gironde.fr/jeunesse/jcms/c_40811/court-metrage-hippocampe|title=D\u00e9partement de la Gironde - Court m\u00e9trage ''Hippocampe''|publisher=jeunesse.gironde.fr |date=2015-10-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://art-dn.wixsite.com/art-dn/hippocampe|title=Site de l'association Art DN - Hippocampe|publisher=art-dn.wixsite.com/art-dn/hippocampe|date=2015-06-02}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\nShortly after Susan was born, Beatie authored his first book, ''Labor of Love: The Story of One Man's Extraordinary Pregnancy'' (2008).{{r|Beatie 2008b}} In ''Labor of Love'', Beatie describes the fight for his right to have a child. ''Publisher's Weekly'' said the book was \"A compelling, unique narrative\". ''Book List'' praised it as \"Unforced and unpretentious,\" and the ''New York Times'' called it \"Defiant and transformative.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thomasbeatie.net |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121116004915/http://www.thomasbeatie.net/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-11-16 |title=Thomas Beatie's official book website |publisher=thomasbeatie.net |accessdate=2013-05-27 }}</ref>\n\n'''Other Works Include'''\n*  Thomas Beatie, \"Labor of Love: Is society ready for this pregnant husband?\" ''The Advocate''{{r|Beatie 2008a}}\n*  Book contribution, ''The New Transsexuals: The Next Step in Human Evolution'' by George Petros, Thomas Beatie, pp.&nbsp;34\u201343<ref>{{cite web|url=http://georgepetros.com/books/tnt.htm#.UVS8Tb-hD0c |title=The New Transsexuals -- The Next Step in Human Evolution, Thomas Beatie, pp. 34-43 (PetrosIdeas, 2012, pp. 34-43) ISBN 978-0-9855018-0-8 |publisher=georgepetros.com |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref>\n*  Swedish newspaper contribution to ''Aftonbladet''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/debatt/article13401439.ab |title=Sweden's Law Would Have Made Me Childless (translated from Swedish)|publisher=aftonbladet.se.com |date=2011-08-01 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref>\n*  Book contribution, ''Gender Identity and Sexual Orientation in the Workplace'' by Christine Duffy<ref>Gender Identity and Sexual Orientation in the Workplace by Christine Duffy, Beyond Binary essay by Thomas Beatie (2013)</ref>\n*  Thomas Beatie, \"Dad v. Scorpion,\" Goodmenproject.com<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goodmenproject.com/featured-content/the-good-life-dad-v-scorpion/ |title='Dad v. Scorpion by Thomas Beatie |publisher=goodmenproject.com |date=2013-01-05 |accessdate=2013-05-27}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and honors ==\n*  [[Barbara Walters]] Top 10 Fascinating People of 2008<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.celebuzz.com/barbara-walters-names-most-fascinating-s68571/ |title=Barbara Walters Names Her Most Fascinating Friends |publisher=celebuzz.com |year=2008 |accessdate=2013-05-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121012141039/http://www.celebuzz.com/barbara-walters-names-most-fascinating-s68571/ |archive-date=2012-10-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*  [[Details (magazine)|''Details'' 