o-to-headline-oberweis-campaign-fundraiser/avrweu5/ |website=Kane County Chronicle |accessdate=March 12, 2020 |date=October 17, 2019}}</ref>\n\n;U.S. Representatives\n*[[Dan Manzullo]], former Representative IL-16 (1993-2013)<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 GOP 6TH & 14TH CONGRESSIONAL CANDIDATES BOAST ENDORSEMENTS |url=https://www.illinoisreview.com/illinoisreview/2020/01/2020-gop-6th-14th-congressional-candidates-boast-endorsements.html |website=Illinois Review |accessdate=March 12, 2020 |date=January 10, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n{{endorsements box\n|title = Sue Rezin\n| width= 68em\n|list =\n;State-wide officials\n* [[Leslie Munger]], former Comptroller of Illinois<ref>{{cite web |title=Endorsements - Sue Rezin for Congress |url=https://rezinforcongress.com/endorsements/ |accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n;Newspapers\n* [[Chicago Tribune]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Editorial: More choices for U.S. House: Quigley, Ives, Davis, Krishnamoorthi, Foster, Bansal ... |url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/opinion/editorials/ct-editorial-us-house2-quigley-ives-davis-londrigan-rezin-20200214-hssynnayavdw7k3m3jfhblk6um-story.html |website=Chicago Tribune |accessdate=March 12, 2020 |date=February 14, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights, Illinois)|Daily Herald]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Endorsement: Rezin for Republicans in House 14th District |url=https://www.dailyherald.com/discuss/20200215/endorsement-rezin-for-republicans-in-house-14th-district |website=Daily Herald |accessdate=March 12, 2020 |date=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results<ref name=ILPrimary /><ref>{{Cite news|title=Illinois Primary Election Results: 14th House District|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2020/03/17/us/elections/results-illinois-house-district-14-primary-election.html|access-date=March 18, 2020|publisher=[[New York Times]]}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidat