hn Shimkus]], who was re-elected with 70.9% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" /> Shimkus announced he would not be seeking re-election on August 30, 2019.<ref name=\"shimkus\">{{cite web |last1=Lally |first1=Caitlin |title=KMOX EXCLUSIVE: Illinois GOP congressman John Shimkus will not run in 2020 |url=https://kmox.radio.com/articles/news/illinois-gop-congressman-john-shimkus-will-not-run-2020 |website=KMOX News Radio |accessdate=August 30, 2019 |date=August 30, 2019}}</ref> After briefly considering reversing his retirement plans, Shimkus reaffirmed his decision to not run on November 4, 2019.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2019/11/04/john-shimkus-retires-congress-065602|title=Rep. John Shimkus sticks to decision to retire from Congress|first=Anthony|last=Adragna|website=POLITICO|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*Mary Miller, [[Oakland, Illinois|Oakland]] farm owner<ref name=\"Ellington\" />\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n*Darren Duncan, [[Vermilion County, Illinois|Vermilion County]] treasurer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vermilioncountyfirst.com/2019/11/10/duncan-announces-hes-running-for-congress/|title=Duncan Announces He's Running for Congress|accessdate=November 23, 2019|publisher=Vermilion County First}}</ref>\n*Charles Ellington, family physician<ref name=\"Ellington\">{{cite web |last1=Sapp |first1=Greg |title=Ellington, Miller Announce Runs for Republican Congressional Nomination |url=http://www.thexradio.com/news/78-local-news/41605-ellington-miller-announce-runs-for-republican-congressional-nomination |website=97.9 XFM |accessdate=October 23, 2019 |date=October 23, 2019}}</ref>\n*Kerry Wolff, vice president of the [[Altamont, Illinois|Altamont]] school board<ref>{{cite web |last1=Perry |first1=Scott |title=Altamont man joins race to replace John Shimkus in Congress |url=https://jg-tc.com/news/state-and-regional/govt-and-politics/altamont-man-joins-race-to-replace-shimkus-in-congress/article_32fedd67-c4a1-527f-8d9d-9a558c793795.html |website=Journal Gazette & Times-Courier |accessdate=October 29, 2019 |date=October 29, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=====Withdrawn=====\n*Alex Walker, U.S. Air Force Veteran<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/alexwalker2020/status/1199036093649297408|title=For immediate release...pic.twitter.com/oQxnxbGG4o|first=\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8Alex|last=Walker #MAGA #KAG&nbsp;\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8|date=November 25, 2019|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=====Declined=====\n*[[Erika Harold]], nominee for [[Illinois Attorney General]] in [[2018 Illinois Attorney General election|2018]] and former [[Miss America 2003|Miss America]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ditman |first1=Tim |title=Harold doesn't plan to make run for Congress |url=https://www.news-gazette.com/news/harold-doesn-t-plan-to-make-run-for-congress/article_6afc2318-d97f-11e9-9fa2-2319d580dfca.html |website=Champaign/Urbana News-Gazette |accessdate=September 17, 2019 |date=September 17, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Michael Marron (politician)|Mike Marron]], state representative<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bustos |first1=Joseph |title=State representative to explore run to replace Shimkus in 15th district |url=https://amp.bnd.com/news/politics-government/election/article234655037.html#referrer=https://www.google.com |website=Belleville News-Democrat |accessdate=September 3, 2019 |date=September 3, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Kyle McCarter]], U.S. Ambassador to Kenya and former state senator<ref name=\"Primarycan\">{{cite web |last1=Bustos |first1=Joseph |title=With Shimkus not running, which notable GOP names will enter the 15th district race? |url=https://www.bnd.com/news/politics-government/election/article235006352.html |website=Belleville News-Democrat |accessdate=September 13, 2019 |date=September 13, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Dale Righter]], state senator<ref name=\"Primarycan\" />\n*[[Chapin Rose]], state senator<ref name=\"Primarycan\" />\n*[[John Shimkus]], i