 Illinois]], taking in the east side of [[Rockford, Illinois|Rockford]], [[Belvidere, Illinois|Belvidere]], [[Ottawa, Illinois|Ottawa]], and [[DeKalb, Illinois|DeKalb]]. The incumbent is Republican [[Adam Kinzinger]], who was re-elected with 59.1% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Adam Kinzinger]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref>{{Cite news|last1=Hinz|first1=Greg|title=Kinzinger set to run for the U.S. House again|url=https://www.chicagobusiness.com/greg-hinz-politics/kinzinger-set-run-us-house-again|website=Crain's Chicago Business|date=August 5, 2019|accessdate=August 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results<ref name=ILPrimary />\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Adam Kinzinger]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = 45296\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 45296\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*Dani Brzozowski, activist and chairwoman of [[LaSalle County, Illinois|LaSalle County]] Democrats<ref>{{cite news|last1=Barichello|first1=David|title=La Salle Democrat to challenge U.S. Rep. Kinzinger in 2020|url=https://www.daily-chronicle.com/2019/09/11/la-salle-democrat-to-challenge-u-s-rep-kinzinger-in-2020/amuyrpx/|date=September 13, 2019|accessdate=September 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results<ref name=ILPrimary />\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Dani Brzozowski\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 50811\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 50811\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Endorsements===\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Dani Brzozowski (D)\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;US Senators\n* [[Dick Durbin]], US Senator for Illinois<ref>https://twitter.com/DaniForCongress/status/1226968007966121986</ref>\n;Unions\n* [[AFL-CIO]] of Illinois<ref>https://twitter.com/DaniForCongress/status/1220055729647902720</ref>\n* Illinois [[American Federation of Teachers|Federation of Teachers]]<ref>https://www.facebook.com/DaniForCongress/photos/a.104390920951913/197971218260549/?type=3&__tn__=-R</ref>\n* Illinois Nurses Association<ref>https://twitter.com/DaniForCongress/status/1234950023525388289</ref>\n* [[Teamsters]] Joint Council 25<ref>https://twitter.com/DaniForCongress/status/1227295974600695810</ref>\n;Organizations\n* DUH! Demand Universal Healthcare<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://duh4all.org/us-house-senate-candidates/|title=2020 Endorsed House Candidates|website=DUH! Demand Universal Healthcare|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Independent Voters of Illinois-Independent Precinct Organization]] (IVI-IPO)<ref>https://twitter.com/DaniForCongress/status/1230579217731063809</ref>\n* [[National Organization for Women|National Organization for Women (NOW)]]<ref>https://twitter.com/NationalNOWPAC/status/1232728725248249857</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Adam Kinzinger (R)\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;Organizations\n*[[Combat Veterans for Congress]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.combatveteransforcongress.org/cand/62|title=Combat Veterans For Congress &#124; Electing Fiscal Conservatives|website=combatveteransforcongress.org|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===General election===\n====Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Illinois's 16th congressional district, 2020\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Dani Brzozowski\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \t\n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Adam Kinzinger]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| vote