tate|state]] of [[Illinois]], one from each of the state's 18 [[Illinois's congressional districts|congressional districts]]. The elections will coincide with the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 U.S. presidential election]], as well as [[United States House of Representatives elections, 2020|other elections]] to the House of Representatives, [[2020 United States Senate elections|elections]] to the [[United States Senate]] and various [[2020 United States elections#State elections|state]] and [[2020 United States elections#Local elections|local elections]].\n{{toclimit|2}}\n\n==District 1==\n{{see also|Illinois's 1st congressional district}}\nThe 1st district takes in the [[South Side, Chicago|South Side]] of [[Chicago]], the southern suburbs of Chicago, and continues southwest to [[Joliet, Illinois|Joliet]]. The incumbent is Democrat [[Bobby Rush]], who was re-elected with 73.5% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\">{{cite web|last1=Wasserman|first1=David|last2=Flinn|first2=Ally|title=2018 House Popular Vote Tracker|url=https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1WxDaxD5az6kdOjJncmGph37z0BPNhV1fNAH_g7IkpC0/htmlview|publisher=Cook Political Report|date=November 7, 2018|accessdate=February 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Bobby Rush]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref name=\"ILcand\"/>\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n*Robert Emmons Jr., nonprofit executive<ref>{{cite news|last1=McQueary|first1=Kristen|title=Column: Ignore Bobby Rush. Kim Foxx's wounds are self-inflicted.|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/opinion/mcqueary/ct-perspec-mcqueary-bobby-rush-kim-foxx-smollett-20190408-story.html|newspaper=Chicago Tribune|date=April 8, 2019|accessdate=April 16, 2019}}</ref>\n*Sarah Gad, law student and opioid recovery advocate<ref>{{cite web|url=https://chicagodefender.com/chicago-activist-announces-run-for-u-s-congress-would-be-nations-first-formerly-incarcerated-woman-elected/|title=Chicago activist Sarah Gad could be nation's first formerly incarcerated women legislator|date=October 28, 2019|accessdate=November 23, 2019|publisher=[[The Chicago Defender]]}}</ref>\n*Ameena Matthews, community activist<ref>{{cite news |last1=Garmes |first1=Kyle |title=Matthews follows activism with run in First District |url=http://www.beverlyreview.net/news/community_news/article_a452c95a-a270-11e9-a03f-bbf661ab607d.html|accessdate=July 9, 2019 |publisher=The Beverly Review |date=July 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Endorsements====\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Bobby Rush\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;Organizations\n* [[Planned Parenthood Action Fund]]<ref name=\"PP\">{{cite web |title=2020 Endorsements |url=https://www.plannedparenthoodaction.org/elections/2020-endorsements#full |website=plannedparenthoodaction.org |publisher=Planned Parenthood Action Fund |language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Sierra Club]]<ref name=\"SierraClub\"/>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Robert Emmons Jr.\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;Newspapers\n*[[The Chicago Maroon]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Endorsement: Robert Emmons, Jr., for Illinois's First Congressional District |url=https://www.chicagomaroon.com/article/2020/2/13/endorsement-robert-emmons-illinoiss-first-congress/ |website=www.chicagomaroon.com |language=en |date=14 February 2020}}</ref>\n*[[The Chicago Tribune]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/opinion/editorials/ct-editorial-us-house-day-one-lipinski-fricilone-emmons-kelly-20200214-zr2r2jvx3nhlldz3oeuwps2dwe-story.html| title=Endorsement: Robert Emmons Jr. Endorsement|website=Chicago Tribune}}</ref>\n;Organizations\n*[[Brand New Congress]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://brandnewcongress.org/Robert-Emmons|title=Robert Emmons|date=October 21, 2019|website=Brand New Congress|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[Sunrise Movement]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Movement |first1=Sunrise |title=Sunrise Movement launches first wave of Congressional primary endorsements, fortifying Green New\u2026 |url=https://medium.com/sunrisemvmt/sunrise-movement-launches-first-wave-of-congressional-primary-endorsements-fortifying-green-new-535a1f21876 |website=Medium |language=en |date=12 December 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results<ref name=ILPrimary>{{cite web|url=https://www.elections.il.gov/ElectionOperations/ElectionVoteTotals.aspx?ID=%2bzMIuj2TEvA%3d&OfficeType=%2brBqro%2b%2bHTUkQvv7Q1tDdQ%3d%3d&T=637227450317589705|title=Election Results 2020 GENERAL PRIMARY|publisher=[[Illinois State Board of Elections]]|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref name=ChicagoDemPrimary>{{Cite web|url=https://chicagoelections.gov/en/election-results.asp?election=230|title=Election Results 2020 Primary - DEM - 3/17/2020|access-date=April 8, 2020|publisher=Chicago Board of Election Commissioners}}</ref><ref name=CookPrimary>{{Cite web|url=https://results320.cookcountyclerk.com/summary.aspx?eid=31720|title=Suburban Cook County Election Results March 17, 2020 Presidential Primary Election|access-date=April 8, 2020|publisher=Cook County Clerk's Office}}</ref><ref name=WillPrimary>{{Cite web|url=https://results.enr.clarityelections.com/IL/Will/102791/web.241347/#/summary?category=C_3|title=WILL COUNTY, ILLINOIS March 17, 2020 GENERAL PRIMARY ELECTION|access-date=April 8, 2020|publisher=Will County Clerk}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box  winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Bobby Rush]] ([[incumbent]])\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 94863\n| percentage = 71.50\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Sarah Gad\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 13783\n| percentage = 10.39\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Robert Emmons Jr.\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 13628\n| percentage = 10.27\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Ameena Matthews\n| party =