 \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==District 2==\n{{see also|Illinois's 2nd congressional district}}\nThe 2nd district encompasses [[South Side Chicago]] and its southern suburbs including eastern [[Will County, Illinois|Will County]] and [[Kankakee County, Illinois|Kankakee County]]. The incumbent is Democrat [[Robin Kelly]] who was re-elected with 81.1% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Robin Kelly]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref name=\"ILcand\">{{cite web |title=Candidate List - GENERAL PRIMARY - 3/17/2020 |url=https://www.elections.il.gov/ElectionOperations/CandidateList.aspx?ElectionID=5myT9Hrw%2fcE%3d&Status=DdSSw6Nhyxg%3d&BallotGroup=c3%2bCspQMDW0%3d&QueryType=CcQXm4UCsmFqbZ2ZLinavFuDxkx55TTO |website=Illinois State Board of Elections |accessdate=December 2, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n*Marcus Lewis, postal worker<ref name=\"ILcand\"/>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results<ref name=ILPrimary /><ref name=ChicagoDemPrimary /><ref name=CookPrimary /><ref name=WillPrimary /><ref name=KankakeePrimary>{{Cite web|url=https://results.enr.clarityelections.com/IL/Kankakee/101647/Web02.245501/#/|title=March 17, 2020 General Primary Election|access-date=2020-04-09|publisher=Kankakee County Clerk}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Election box  winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Robin Kelly]] ([[incumbent]])\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 94767\n| percentage = 84.83\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Marcus Lewis \n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = 16942\n| percentage = 15.17\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 111709\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*Theresa Raborn, activist<ref name=\"ILcand\"/>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results<ref name=ILPrimary /><ref name=ChicagoGOPPrimary /><ref name=CookPrimary /><ref name=WillPrimary /><ref name=KankakeePrimary />\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Theresa Raborn\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = 12181\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = 12181\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===General election===\n====Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Illinois's 2nd congressional district, 2020\n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Robin Kelly]] ([[incumbent]])\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \t\n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Theresa Raborn\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \t\n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes =\n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==District 3==\n{{see also|Illinois's 3rd congressional district}}\nThe 3rd district includes western and southwestern suburbs of [[Chicago]] as far as the [[DuPage County, Illinois|DuPage County]] border, as well part of southwest Chicago itself. The incumbent is Democrat [[Dan Lipinski]], who was re-elected with 73.0% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" /> On March 17, 2020, Marie Newman defeated Dan Lipinski in the Democratic primary. \n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Marie Newman]], businesswoman and candidate for [[Illinois's 3rd congressional district]] in 2018<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sweet|first1=Lynn|title=Marie Newman officially jumps in Democratic primary against Rep. Dan Lipinski|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/news/marie-newman-officially-jumps-in-democratic-primary-against-rep-dan-lipinski/|newspaper=Chicago Sun-Times|date=April 16, 2019|accessdate=April 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n*Rush Darwish, photographer and former broadcaster<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ortiz |first1=Alex |title=Small business owner, former broadcaster launches challenge to Lipinski in 2020 |url=https://www.theherald-news.com/2019/05/28/small-business-owner-former-broadcaster-launches-challenge-to-lipinski-in-2020/a5h2yca/ |accessdate=May 28, 2019 |publisher=The Times-Herald |date=May 28, 2019}}</ref>\n*Charles Hughes<ref name=\"Jones\"/>\n*[[Dan Lipinski]], incumbent U.S. Representative<ref name=\"auto\">[https://www.elections.il.gov/ElectionOperations/CandidatesFiled.aspx?MID=3f5BmPC%2bbZA%3d&T=637104998747872970 Candidates Filed<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and former political science professor<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ballotpedia.org/Daniel_Lipinski|title=Daniel Lipinski|website=Ballotpedia}}</ref>\n\n=====Withdrawn=====\n*Abe Matthew, attorney<ref>{{cite news|last1=Sweet|first1=Lynn|title=Lipinski challenger drops out, endorses Newman in Democratic primary for Congress|url=https://chicago.suntimes.com/columnists/2019/11/12/20960673/lipinski-abe-matthew-drops-out-endorses-marie-newman-illinois-congress-democratic-primary|newspaper=Chicago Sun Times|date=November 12, 2019}}</ref> (''endorsed Newman'')\n\n=====Endorsements=====\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Dan Lipinski\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n; U.S. Senators\n*[[Joe Manchin]], U.S. Senator from West Virginia and former Governor of West Virginia <ref name=\"Democrats for Life Board\">{{Cite web | url=https://www.democratsforlife.org/index.php/about-us/advisory-boards |title=Democrats for Life |website=democratsforlife.org |accessdate=January 28, 2020}}</ref>\n; U.S. Representatives\n* [[Bill Lipinski]], former US Representative from Illinois's 3rd congressional district and Lipinski's father\n* [[Nancy Pelosi]], [[Speaker of the United States House of Representatives]], Representative from [[California's 12th congressional district]] <ref name= \"Democrats Rally Behind Incumbents\">{{Ci