ominee=====\n*Betsy Dirksen Londrigan, former nonprofit leader, entrepreneur, and nominee for Illinois's 13th congressional district in [[2018 United States House of Representatives elections in Illinois#District 13|2018]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Schoenburg|first1=Bernard|title=Londrigan to take on Davis again in 13th|url=https://www.sj-r.com/news/20190411/londrigan-to-take-on-davis-again-in-13th|newspaper=The State Journal-Register|date=April 11, 2019|accessdate=April 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=====Eliminated in Primary=====\n*Stefanie Smith, former sex worker and activist<ref>{{cite web |last1=Denham |first1=Ryan |last2=Newgent |first2=Sean |title=Second Democrat In 13th District Race Backs Single-Payer Health Care, Green New Deal |url=https://will.illinois.edu/news/story/second-democrat-in-13th-district-race-backs-single-payer-health-care-green-new-deal |website=Illinois Public Media |accessdate=November 24, 2019 |date=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Endorsements====\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Betsy Dirksen Londrigan\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;US Senators\n*[[Dick Durbin]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailykos.com/story/2019/4/25/1853255/-IL-13-Sen-Dick-Durbin-D-Helps-Betsy-Dirksen-Londrigan-D-Get-Ready-To-Unseat-Rodney-Davis-R|title=IL-13: Sen. Dick Durbin (D) Helps Betsy Dirksen Londrigan (D) Get Ready To Unseat Rodney Davis (R)|website=Daily Kos}}</ref>\n;Labor Unions\n* Illinois [[AFL-CIO]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Illinois State COPE|url=http://www.ilafl-cio.org/political.htm|website=Illinois AFL-CIO|date=January 15, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[International Brotherhood of Electrical Workers]]<ref name=\"LondriganEndorsements1\">{{cite web |last1=Miller|first1=Rich|title=Congressional roundup|url=https://capitolfax.com/2020/01/07/congressional-roundup-15/|website=Capitol Fax|date=January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[United Food and Commercial Workers]]<ref name=\"LondriganEndorsements1\"/>\n*[[United Steelworkers]]<ref name=\"LondriganEndorsements1\"/>\n;Organizations\n* [[Bend the A