27295974600695810</ref>\n;Organizations\n* DUH! Demand Universal Healthcare<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://duh4all.org/us-house-senate-candidates/|title=2020 Endorsed House Candidates|website=DUH! Demand Universal Healthcare|accessdate=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Independent Voters of Illinois-Independent Precinct Organization]] (IVI-IPO)<ref>https://twitter.com/DaniForCongress/status/1230579217731063809</ref>\n* [[National Organization for Women|National Organization for Women (NOW)]]<ref>https://twitter.com/NationalNOWPAC/status/1232728725248249857</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Adam Kinzinger (R)\n| width= 68em\n| list =\n;Organizations\n*[[Combat Veterans for Congress]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.combatveteransforcongress.org/cand/62|title=Combat Veterans For Congress &#124; Electing Fiscal Conservatives|website=combatveteransforcongress.org|accessdate=January 12, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===General election===\n====Results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Illinois's 16th congressional district, 2020\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Dani Brzozowski\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \t\n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box  candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Adam Kinzinger]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \t\n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==District 17==\n{{see also|Illinois's 17th congressional district}}\nThe 17th district encompasses [[northwestern Illinois]], including the [[Quad Cities|Quad cities metro]], the westside of [[Rockford, Illinois|Rockford]], and [[Peoria, Illinois|Peoria]]. The incumbent is Democrat [[Cheri Bustos]], who was re-elected with 62.1% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\" />\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Nominee=====\n*[[Cheri Bustos]], incumbent U.S. Representative\n*Spanky Edwards, chairman of th