 | title = Suburban Escape: The Art of California Sprawl}}</ref>\n* 2010: ''Pier 24: The Inaugural Exhibition'', [[Pier 24 Photography]], San Francisco, CA, March\u2013June 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pier24.org/exhibition/pier-24-the-inaugural-exhibition/|title=Pier 24: The Inaugural Exhibition \u2013 Pier 24|website=Pier24.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* 2010: ''Day & Night,'' Main Exhibition Copenhagen Photo Festival, Copenhagen, Denmark.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://copenhagenphotofestival.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/CPF-PRESS.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-06-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150915092646/http://copenhagenphotofestival.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/CPF-PRESS.pdf |archivedate=2015-09-15 }}</ref>\n* 2011\u20132012: ''Here''., [[Pier 24 Photography]], San Francisco, CA, May 2011 \u2013 January 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pier24.org/exhibition/here/|title=Here. - Pier 24|website=Pier24.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* 2012\u20132013: ''About Face'', [[Pier 24 Photography]], San Francisco, CA, May 2012 \u2013 April 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pier24.org/exhibition/about-face/|title=About Face \u2013 Pier 24|website=Pier24.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* 2013\u20132014: ''A Sense of Place'', [[Pier 24 Photography]], San Francisco, CA, July 2013 \u2013 May 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pier24.org/exhibition/a-sense-of-place/|title=A Sense of Place \u2013 Pier 24|website=Pier24.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* 2016: ''The Open Road: Photography and the American Road Trip,'' [[Crystal Bridges Museum of American Art]], Bentonville, AR, February\u2013May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://crystalbridges.org/the-open-road/|title=The Open Road \u2013 Crystal Bridges Museum of American Art|website=crystalbridges.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref> Curated by [[David Campany]] and Denise Wolff.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://aperture.org/traveling-exhibitions/open-road/ | access-date = 11 March 2016 | publisher = [[Aperture Foundation]] | title = The Open Road: Photography and the American Road Trip: Curated by David Campany and Denise Wolff}}</ref>\n* 2016\u20132017: ''Collected'', Pier 24 Photography, San Francisco, CA, May 2016 \u2013 January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pier24.org/exhibitions/|title=Exhibitions \u2013 Pier 24|website=Pier24.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Awards ==\n* 1996: Barclay Simpson Award, [[California College of the Arts]], CA. Joinet winner with [[Geoffrey Chadsey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://issuu.com/californiacollegeofthearts/docs/barclay25_catalog_lowres|title=Celebrating 25 Years of the Barclay Simpson Award|website=Issuu.com|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cca.edu/calendar/2012/barclay-simpson-award-retrospective-exhibition-1987-2012|title=We're All Here Because We're Not All There \u2013 California College of the Arts|website=Cca.edu|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* 1998: The Wallace Alexander Gerbode Foundation, Visual Arts Award.<ref group=\"n\">The Wallace Alexander Gerbode Foundation's \"Special Awards Recipients 1987-Present\" PDF [http://foundationcenter.org/grantmaker/gerbode/docs/1987-Present-Recipients.pdf here] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150908025301/http://www.foundationcenter.org/grantmaker/gerbode/docs/1987-Present-Recipients.pdf |date=2015-09-08 }} does not list Hido.</ref>\n* 1998: Recent Graduate of Distinction Award, California College of the Arts, CA.{{citation needed|date=October 2015}}\n* 2001: Eureka Fellowship, Fleishhacker Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fleishhackerfoundation.org/grants/eureka-fellowship-program/1999-2001/|title=The Fleishhacker Foundation \u2013 1999\u20132001|website=Fleishhackerfoundation.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* 2002: Best First Monograph of 2001, Photo-Eye.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.photoeye.com/bookstore/citation.cfm?catalog=PK802&i=3902289015&i2=|title=photo-eye Bookstore \u2013 Architecture of Time by Hiroshi Sugimoto \u2013 photobook|website=Photoeye.com|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* 2017: In Focus Artist selected by the National Portrait Gallery UK curators, an annual showcase for new work by an internationally renowned photographer <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npg.org.uk/whatson/event-root/november/in-conversation-13112017|title=In Conversation: Todd Hido \u2013 National Portrait Gallery|website=Npg.org.uk|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Collections ==\nHido's work is held in the following public collections:\n{{col-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Art Institute of Chicago]], IL.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artic.edu/aic/collections/artwork/artist/Hido,+Todd|title=Hido, Todd \u2013 The Art Institute of Chicago|website=Artic.edu|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Amon Carter Museum of American Art]], Fort Worth, TX.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cartermuseum.org/artworks/779|title=Untitled #2431 \u2013 Todd Hido (b. 1968)|date=6 June 2008|website=Cartermuseum.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Berkeley Art Museum and Pacific Film Archive]], Berkeley, CA.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2018-04-05|title=This Just In: Recent Acquisitions: BAMPFA|url=https://bampfa.org/program/just-recent-acquisitions|website=bampfa.org}}</ref>\n* [[Cleveland Museum of Art]], Cleveland, OH.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.clevelandart.org/art/2003.9|title=Untitled #2421 \u2013 Cleveland Museum of Art|website=Clevelandart.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Di rosa]], Napa, CA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dirosaart.org/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/Know-the-Rules-_PR.pdf|format=PDF|title=Know the Rules \u2013 Then Break Them Photography from the di Rosa Collection|website=Dirosaart.org\\accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* [[George Eastman House]], Rochester, NY: 6 prints.<ref>https://collections.eastman.org/people/31393/todd-hido/objects</ref>\n* [[Kemper Museum of Contemporary Art]], Kansas City, MO.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kemperart.org/exhibits/CatalogEssays/hidotodd.asp|title=Kemper Museum of Art Exhibitions|publisher=Kemperart.org|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Los Angeles County Museum of Art]], CA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collections.lacma.org/node/159411|title=Todd Hido \u2013 LACMA Collections|website=collections.lacma.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Madison Museum of Contemporary Art]], Madison, WI.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mmoca.org/mmocacollects/artist_page.php?id=13 |title=The MMoCA Collects Site Has Moved |publisher=MMoCA |accessdate=2014-04-19 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419212451/http://www.mmoca.org/mmocacollects/artist_page.php?id=13 |archivedate=2014-04-19 }}</ref>\n* [[Museum of Contemporary Photography]], Chicago, IL.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2018-04-05|title=Museum of Contemporary Photography|url=http://www.mocp.org/detail.php?t=objects&type=browse&f=maker&s=Hido%252C+Todd&record=0|website=www.mocp.org}}</ref>\n* [[Museum of Fine Arts, Boston]], MA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mfa.org/collections/object/3235-479742|title=3235|date=3 April 2017|website=Mfa.org|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Museum of Fine Arts, Houston]], TX.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2018-04-05|title=Untitled #2312-a |url=https://www.mfah.org/art/detail/76295?returnUrl=%252Fart%252Fsearch%253Fartist%253DTodd%252BHido%2526nationality%253DAmerican|website=www.mfah.org}}</ref>\n* [[National Science and Media Museum]], Bradford, UK: 2 prints<ref>https://collection.sciencemuseum.org.uk/people/cp134355/todd-hido</ref>\n* [[New York Public Library]], NY.<ref name=\"nypl\">\"[https://www.nypl.org/sites/default/files/Photographers_in_The_New_York_Public_Library_April_16_2010.pdf Photographers in The New York Public Library's Photography Collection]\". [[New York Public Library]]. Accessed 5 April 2018.</ref>\n* [[North Carolina Museum of Art]], Raleigh, NC.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2018-04-05|title=Search \u2013 Permanent Collection \u2013 NCMA \u2013 North Carolina Museum of Art|url=http://ncartmuseum.org/art/search|website=ncartmuseum.org}}</ref>\n*[[Pier 24 Photography]], San Francisco, CA.<ref>https://pier24.org/collection/</ref>\n* [[San Francisco Museum of Modern Art]], San Francisco, CA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sfmoma.org/artist/Todd_Hido|title=Todd Hido|website=SFMOMA|accessdate=14 December 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Whitney Museum of American Art]], NY.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2018-04-05|title=Whitney Museum of American Art: Todd Hido: #2663|url=http://collection.whitney.org/object/27261|website=collection.whitney.org}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== Notes ==\n<references group=\"n\" />\n\n== Sources ==\n* [http://www.clevelandart.org/educef/hido/index.aspx Berwick, Carly. Todd Hido: Julie Saul, ART news, November, pp.&nbsp;153\u2013154. 2004.]{{dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}\n* [http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_hb3202/is_200110/ai_n7879833?tag=content;col1: Helfand, Glen. Todd Hido. (Stephen Wirtz), Artforum International, October 2001.]\n* [http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0268/is_n9_v36/ai_n27533113/pg_1 Grundberg, Andy. House sitting: the photography of Todd Hido, Artforum, May 1998.]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official website|www.toddhido.com}}\n* [http://pier24.org/video/todd-hido-house-hunting/ Pier 24 Photography Artist Video: Todd Hido]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20131003045644/http://kadist.org/en/people/todd-hido Todd Hido] at [[Kadist Art Foundation]]\n* [http://www.ahornmagazine.com/issue_6/interview_hido/interview_hido.html Interview with Todd Hido \u2013 Ahorn Magazine, Issue 6]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=embdo2Er19A 'Working in the Vicinity of Narrative: Todd Hido and Darius Himes'] from School of Visual Arts. Hido presentation of his career (video)\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hido, Todd}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\